1
00:00:47,047 --> 00:00:50,300
(CELTIC FLUTE MUSIC PLAYING)

2
00:01:11,321 --> 00:01:12,739
(BIRDSONG)

3
00:01:19,621 --> 00:01:23,083
Where are you? Come out!

4
00:01:23,166 --> 00:01:25,252
Come out! (LAUGHS)

5
00:01:26,128 --> 00:01:28,088
Come on out.

6
00:01:28,171 --> 00:01:29,464
(GIGGLES)

7
00:01:29,506 --> 00:01:33,176
- I'm coming to get you.
- (GIGGLES)

8
00:01:34,469 --> 00:01:37,514
Where are you, you little rascal?
I'm coming to get you.

9
00:01:37,556 --> 00:01:39,516
Hm. (CHUCKLES)

10
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:42,311
Where is my little birthday girl, hm?

11
00:01:43,186 --> 00:01:46,481
I'm going to gobble her up
when I find her.

12
00:01:46,523 --> 00:01:48,358
- Oh! (LAUGHS)
- (SQUEALS)

13
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:50,360
I'm going to eat you. I am.

14
00:01:50,444 --> 00:01:52,404
(MAKES MUNCHING NOISES)

15
00:01:52,487 --> 00:01:55,991
Och, Fergus, no weapons on the table.

16
00:01:56,033 --> 00:01:58,243
Can I shoot an arrow?
Can I? Can I? Can I? Can I?

17
00:01:58,327 --> 00:02:00,537
Please? Can I? (LAUGHS)

18
00:02:00,621 --> 00:02:03,665
- Not with that. Why not...
- (GIGGLES)

19
00:02:03,707 --> 00:02:05,042
...use your very own?

20
00:02:05,125 --> 00:02:08,420
- (GASPS)
- Happy birthday, my wee darling!

21
00:02:09,046 --> 00:02:10,047
(BOW BEING PLUCKED)

22
00:02:12,299 --> 00:02:14,384
- Now, there's a good girl.
- (STRAINS)

23
00:02:14,426 --> 00:02:17,012
Draw all the way back now
to your cheek. That's right.

24
00:02:18,305 --> 00:02:20,307
Keep both eyes open.

25
00:02:21,266 --> 00:02:23,268
And, loose!

26
00:02:25,395 --> 00:02:27,397
- I missed.
- Go and fetch it, then.

27
00:02:29,733 --> 00:02:32,694
A bow, Fergus? She's a lady.

28
00:02:32,944 --> 00:02:34,821
- Ooh! You!
- (LAUGHS)

29
00:02:43,205 --> 00:02:45,499
(BIRDS CALLING)

30
00:02:58,345 --> 00:03:00,347
(CREAKING)

31
00:03:02,557 --> 00:03:04,434
(LONE BIRD CALLS)

32
00:03:05,268 --> 00:03:07,104
(HEAVY BREATHING)

33
00:03:09,022 --> 00:03:11,024
(HIGH-PITCHED CALL)

34
00:03:12,234 --> 00:03:13,276
A will-o'-the-wisp.

35
00:03:15,946 --> 00:03:17,531
(GROWLING)

36
00:03:21,576 --> 00:03:23,704
They are real.

37
00:03:31,670 --> 00:03:34,297
ELINOR:
Merida, come along, sweetheart.

38
00:03:34,339 --> 00:03:36,508
- We're leaving now.
- MERIDA: I saw a wisp.

39
00:03:38,510 --> 00:03:40,637
- I saw a wisp.
- A wisp?

40
00:03:40,679 --> 00:03:46,017
You know, some say that
will-o'-the-wisps lead you to your fate.

41
00:03:46,101 --> 00:03:48,562
- Oh, aye. Or an arrow.
- Och!

42
00:03:48,645 --> 00:03:51,648
Come on, let's be off before we see
a dancing Tatty Bogle.

43
00:03:51,732 --> 00:03:54,151
Or a giant having a jigger
in the bluebells.

44
00:03:54,234 --> 00:03:56,153
Your father doesn't believe in magic.

45
00:03:56,194 --> 00:03:58,655
Well, he should. Because it's true.

46
00:03:58,697 --> 00:04:00,073
(GASPS)
(SCREAMS)

47
00:04:00,157 --> 00:04:01,616
(GROWLS)

48
00:04:01,658 --> 00:04:03,368
Mor'du! Elinor, run!

49
00:04:03,452 --> 00:04:05,412
- (ROARS)
- Sire!

50
00:04:05,495 --> 00:04:07,497
(YELLS)

51
00:04:10,625 --> 00:04:11,625
(SNARLS)

52
00:04:14,087 --> 00:04:15,172
Come on, you!

53
00:04:15,255 --> 00:04:16,255
(ROARS)

54
00:04:28,685 --> 00:04:31,813
MERIDA: <i>Some say our destiny
is tied to the land...</i>

55
00:04:32,856 --> 00:04:35,358
<i>...as much a part of us as we are of it.</i>

56
00:04:38,695 --> 00:04:42,532
<i>Others say fate is woven together
like a cloth.</i>

57
00:04:42,616 --> 00:04:44,075
(THUNDER RUMBLES)

58
00:04:44,159 --> 00:04:47,370
<i>So that one's destiny intertwines
with many others.</i>

59
00:04:51,583 --> 00:04:56,379
<i>It's the one thing we search for
or fight to change.</i>

60
00:04:58,173 --> 00:05:00,175
<i>Some never find it.</i>

61
00:05:02,427 --> 00:05:05,555
<i>But there are some who are led.</i>

62
00:05:10,477 --> 00:05:11,478
(YELLS)

63
00:05:11,561 --> 00:05:13,313
<i>The story of how my father lost his leg</i>

64
00:05:14,397 --> 00:05:15,917
<i>to the demon bear Mor'du
became legend.</i>

65
00:05:16,983 --> 00:05:18,151
(GROANING)

66
00:05:19,152 --> 00:05:21,696
<i>I became a sister to three new brothers.</i>

67
00:05:21,738 --> 00:05:24,741
<i>The princes.
Hamish, Hubert and Harris.</i>

68
00:05:25,408 --> 00:05:27,744
<i>Wee devils, more like.</i>

69
00:05:27,828 --> 00:05:30,330
<i>They get away with murder.</i>

70
00:05:30,413 --> 00:05:32,666
<i>I can never get away with anything.</i>

71
00:05:34,626 --> 00:05:36,670
<i>I'm the princess.</i>

72
00:05:36,753 --> 00:05:38,380
- Oh!
- (BAGPIPES PLAYING)

73
00:05:38,421 --> 00:05:40,423
<i>MERIDA: I'm the example.</i>

74
00:05:41,383 --> 00:05:42,425
(SLURPS)

75
00:05:42,467 --> 00:05:45,428
<i>I've got duties, responsibilities,
expectations.</i>

76
00:05:45,512 --> 00:05:47,305
<i>My whole life is planned out,</i>

77
00:05:47,389 --> 00:05:49,349
<i>preparing for the day I become...</i>

78
00:05:49,432 --> 00:05:50,851
<i>Well, my mother.</i>

79
00:05:50,934 --> 00:05:53,770
<i>She's in charge
of every single day of my life.</i>

80
00:05:53,854 --> 00:05:55,856
- (BAGPIPES CEASE)
- (SIGHS)

81
00:05:57,232 --> 00:06:00,735
"Aye, Robin, Jolly Robin,
and thou shalt know of mine."

82
00:06:00,777 --> 00:06:01,903
Project!

83
00:06:02,153 --> 00:06:03,905
"And thou shalt know of mine!"

84
00:06:04,155 --> 00:06:07,534
Enunciate. You must be understood
from anywhere in the room,

85
00:06:07,617 --> 00:06:09,244
or it's all for naught.

86
00:06:09,286 --> 00:06:11,788
- This is all for naught.
- I heard that!

87
00:06:11,872 --> 00:06:13,415
- (SIGHS)
- From the top.

88
00:06:13,456 --> 00:06:16,418
A princess must be knowledgeable
about her kingdom.

89
00:06:17,961 --> 00:06:19,963
She does not doodle.

90
00:06:20,505 --> 00:06:22,507
(PLAYS NOTES)

91
00:06:22,591 --> 00:06:24,593
That's a C, dear.

92
00:06:27,262 --> 00:06:29,389
(SCREECHES)
(SCREAMS)

93
00:06:29,472 --> 00:06:31,266
(LAUGHS AND SNORTS)

94
00:06:31,308 --> 00:06:33,393
A princess does not chortle.

95
00:06:33,476 --> 00:06:35,520
- Mm!
- Does not stuff her gob!

96
00:06:35,604 --> 00:06:37,314
Rises early.

97
00:06:37,397 --> 00:06:39,190
- ...is compassionate...
- (CHICKEN SQUAWKS)

98
00:06:39,274 --> 00:06:40,692
...patient, cautious,

99
00:06:40,775 --> 00:06:41,776
clean.

100
00:06:41,818 --> 00:06:48,825
And above all, a princess
strives for... Well, perfection.

101
00:06:50,452 --> 00:06:51,995
<i>MERIDA: But every once in a While,</i>

102
00:06:52,245 --> 00:06:56,833
<i>there's a day
when I don't have to be a princess.</i>

103
00:06:59,461 --> 00:07:01,922
<i>No lessons, no expectations.</i>

104
00:07:02,005 --> 00:07:04,341
<i>A day Where anything can happen.</i>

105
00:07:05,926 --> 00:07:08,929
<i>A day I can change my fate.</i>

106
00:07:09,012 --> 00:07:10,221
<i>Yah!</i>

107
00:07:18,855 --> 00:07:20,857
(LIVELY MUSIC PLAYING)

108
00:07:21,066 --> 00:07:27,072
♪ <i>When cold wind is a' calling, ♪
♪ and the sky is clear and bright</i> ♪

109
00:07:27,155 --> 00:07:32,827
♪ <i>Misty mountains sing and beckon, ♪
♪ lead me out into the light</i> ♪

110
00:07:33,203 --> 00:07:36,164
♪ <i>I will ride, I will fly</i> ♪

111
00:07:36,206 --> 00:07:39,209
♪ <i>Chase the wind and touch the sky</i> ♪

112
00:07:39,250 --> 00:07:44,923
♪ <i>I will fly ♪
♪ Chase the wind and touch the sky</i> ♪

113
00:07:50,053 --> 00:07:52,055
Whoo-hoo!

114
00:07:59,229 --> 00:08:00,313
(EAGLE CALLS)

115
00:08:00,397 --> 00:08:06,403
♪ <i>Where dark woods hide secrets ♪
♪ and mountains are fierce and bold</i> ♪

116
00:08:06,486 --> 00:08:12,450
♪ <i>Deep waters hold reflections ♪
♪ of times lost long ago</i> ♪

117
00:08:12,534 --> 00:08:16,496
♪ <i>I will read every story, ♪
♪ take hold of my own dream</i> ♪

118
00:08:16,579 --> 00:08:18,581
- Oh!
- (HORSE WHINNIES)

119
00:08:18,623 --> 00:08:21,751
♪ <i>Be as strong as the seas are stormy</i> ♪

120
00:08:21,793 --> 00:08:24,587
♪ <i>And proud as an eagle's scream</i> ♪

121
00:08:24,629 --> 00:08:27,590
♪ <i>I will ride, I will fly</i> ♪

122
00:08:27,674 --> 00:08:30,593
♪ <i>Chase the wind and touch the sky</i> ♪

123
00:08:30,677 --> 00:08:36,433
♪ <i>I will fly ♪
♪ Chase the wind and touch the sky</i> ♪

124
00:08:45,025 --> 00:08:47,027
(SCREAMS EXCITEDLY)

125
00:08:47,110 --> 00:08:48,945
♪ <i>And touch the sky</i> ♪

126
00:08:49,029 --> 00:08:51,031
Whoo!

127
00:08:52,824 --> 00:08:54,284
♪ <i>Chase the wind</i> ♪

128
00:08:54,325 --> 00:08:57,328
♪ <i>Chase the wind</i> ♪

129
00:08:57,412 --> 00:09:02,584
♪ <i>Touch the sky</i> ♪

130
00:09:09,841 --> 00:09:10,967
(WHINNIES)

131
00:09:11,051 --> 00:09:14,345
I'm starving. You hungry too, Angus?

132
00:09:14,804 --> 00:09:15,805
Pfft!

133
00:09:15,889 --> 00:09:17,849
- Oats it is, then.
- (SNORTS)

134
00:09:20,060 --> 00:09:21,728
Good day, Princess.

135
00:09:21,811 --> 00:09:23,688
I cannot find the salt.
Where did you put it?

136
00:09:23,772 --> 00:09:26,172
It was over there a minute ago,
the last time I looked at it.

137
00:09:26,775 --> 00:09:31,738
And then, out of nowhere,
the biggest bear you've ever seen!

138
00:09:31,821 --> 00:09:34,991
His hide littered with the weapons
of fallen warriors.

139
00:09:35,033 --> 00:09:38,661
His face scarred with one dead eye.

140
00:09:39,454 --> 00:09:41,081
I drew my sword and...

141
00:09:41,164 --> 00:09:42,707
Whoosh!

142
00:09:42,791 --> 00:09:44,918
One swipe, his sword shattered.

143
00:09:45,001 --> 00:09:48,129
Then "chomp"! Dad's leg was clean off.

144
00:09:48,505 --> 00:09:50,882
Down the monster's throat it went.

145
00:09:50,965 --> 00:09:53,885
Oh, that's my favorite part.

146
00:09:53,968 --> 00:09:57,222
Mor'du has never been seen since,

147
00:09:57,347 --> 00:10:02,811
and is roaming the wilds
waiting his chance of revenge.

148
00:10:02,852 --> 00:10:05,355
- (ROARING)
- Let him return.

149
00:10:05,438 --> 00:10:07,524
I'll finish what I guddled in the first place.

150
00:10:07,565 --> 00:10:11,361
Merida, a princess does not place
her weapons on the table.

151
00:10:11,444 --> 00:10:14,656
Mum! It's just my bow.

152
00:10:14,697 --> 00:10:17,700
A princess should not have weapons
in my opinion.

153
00:10:17,742 --> 00:10:19,077
FERGUS: Leave her be.

154
00:10:19,369 --> 00:10:22,038
Princess or not,
learning to fight is essential.

155
00:10:22,122 --> 00:10:24,916
Mum?
You'll never guess what I did today.

156
00:10:24,999 --> 00:10:27,168
- Hm?
- I climbed the Crone's Tooth,

157
00:10:27,418 --> 00:10:28,711
and drank from the Fire Falls.

158
00:10:29,254 --> 00:10:30,672
Fire Falls?

159
00:10:30,713 --> 00:10:34,509
They say only the ancient kings
were brave enough to drink the fire.

160
00:10:34,551 --> 00:10:35,552
(LAUGHS)

161
00:10:35,635 --> 00:10:38,429
- What did you do, dear?
- Nothing, Mum.

162
00:10:38,513 --> 00:10:39,973
Hungry, aren't we?

163
00:10:40,056 --> 00:10:42,433
- Mum!
- You'll get dreadful collywobbles.

164
00:10:42,517 --> 00:10:45,520
Oh, Fergus, will you look at
your daughter's plate?

165
00:10:45,562 --> 00:10:47,564
- (DOGS BARKING)
- So what?

166
00:10:47,605 --> 00:10:50,108
- Oh, you great...
- Don't let them lick... (SIGHS)

167
00:10:50,191 --> 00:10:51,526
Boys, you're naughty.

168
00:10:51,568 --> 00:10:53,653
Don't just play with your haggis.

169
00:10:53,903 --> 00:10:56,698
- Urgh! (GAGGING)
- Och, how do you know you don't like it,

170
00:10:56,739 --> 00:10:58,825
if you won't try it?

171
00:10:58,908 --> 00:11:00,743
That's just a wee sheep's stomach.

172
00:11:00,827 --> 00:11:03,454
It's delicious. Mm! (SMACKS LIPS)

173
00:11:03,538 --> 00:11:05,832
- My lady.
- Thank you, Maudie.

174
00:11:05,915 --> 00:11:07,755
FERGUS: You're getting too big,
the two of you.

175
00:11:11,796 --> 00:11:13,089
ELINOR: Aha.

176
00:11:13,173 --> 00:11:15,550
From the Lords Macintosh,
MacGuffin and Dingwall.

177
00:11:15,592 --> 00:11:16,968
Their responses, no doubt.

178
00:11:17,051 --> 00:11:18,595
Aye, aye!

179
00:11:18,636 --> 00:11:20,638
- FERGUS: Hey, hey! (LAUGHS)
- (MUNCHING LOUDLY)

180
00:11:21,514 --> 00:11:24,184
Stay out of my food,
you greedy mongrels.

181
00:11:24,851 --> 00:11:26,978
Chew on that, you manky dogs!

182
00:11:27,061 --> 00:11:29,105
- (FERGUS LAUGHS)
- Fergus?

183
00:11:31,649 --> 00:11:32,859
They've all accepted.

184
00:11:32,942 --> 00:11:34,944
(DOGS SLOBBERING)

185
00:11:35,612 --> 00:11:37,822
Who's accepted what, Mother?

186
00:11:37,906 --> 00:11:40,116
Boys, you are excused.

187
00:11:40,825 --> 00:11:41,868
(GIGGLING)

188
00:11:42,952 --> 00:11:44,078
- Oof!
- (DOGS BARKING)

189
00:11:44,746 --> 00:11:46,039
Hey! (LAUGHS)

190
00:11:46,998 --> 00:11:49,834
What did I do now?

191
00:11:49,918 --> 00:11:52,128
Your father has something
to discuss with you.

192
00:11:54,631 --> 00:11:55,798
Fergus?

193
00:11:56,633 --> 00:11:58,509
Oh. (CLEARS THROAT)

194
00:11:58,593 --> 00:12:00,261
(COUGHS)

195
00:12:00,511 --> 00:12:03,723
Er... Merida.

196
00:12:06,768 --> 00:12:11,898
(SIGHS) The lords are presenting
their sons as suitors for your betrothal.

197
00:12:11,981 --> 00:12:14,817
- What?
- The clans have accepted.

198
00:12:15,485 --> 00:12:17,987
- Dad!
- What? (STAMMERS) I...

199
00:12:18,029 --> 00:12:20,198
You... She... Elinor?

200
00:12:20,281 --> 00:12:22,867
Honestly, Merida, I don't know why
you're reacting this way.

201
00:12:22,951 --> 00:12:23,952
(SIGHS IN FRUSTRATION)

202
00:12:23,993 --> 00:12:27,997
This year, each clan will present a suitor
to compete in the games for your hand.

203
00:12:28,039 --> 00:12:30,792
I suppose a princess
just does what she's told?

204
00:12:30,833 --> 00:12:33,253
A princess does not raise her voice.

205
00:12:34,087 --> 00:12:37,131
Merida, this is what you've been
preparing for your whole life.

206
00:12:37,674 --> 00:12:41,094
No, it's what you've been preparing
me for my whole life.

207
00:12:41,177 --> 00:12:43,513
I won't go through with it.
You can't make me.

208
00:12:43,596 --> 00:12:45,723
Merida!

209
00:12:45,932 --> 00:12:47,767
Huh? Merida!

210
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:51,521
- Urgh!
- (DOGS BARKING)

211
00:12:51,604 --> 00:12:53,856
Boys!

212
00:12:54,816 --> 00:12:56,818
(GRUNTING)

213
00:12:58,027 --> 00:13:01,739
Mother. Suitors? Marriage?

214
00:13:01,823 --> 00:13:04,200
Once there was an ancient kingdom...

215
00:13:04,242 --> 00:13:06,869
Oh, Mum!

216
00:13:06,953 --> 00:13:08,579
Ancient kingdom.

217
00:13:08,663 --> 00:13:10,707
Its name long forgotten,

218
00:13:11,291 --> 00:13:15,295
ruled by a wise and fair king
who was much beloved.

219
00:13:15,795 --> 00:13:20,800
And when he grew old he divided
the kingdom among his four sons,

220
00:13:20,883 --> 00:13:25,263
that they should be the pillars
on which the peace of the land rested.

221
00:13:26,639 --> 00:13:31,686
But the oldest prince
wanted to rule the land for himself.

222
00:13:31,728 --> 00:13:35,315
He followed his own path
and the kingdom fell

223
00:13:36,607 --> 00:13:39,569
to war, and chaos and ruin.

224
00:13:39,652 --> 00:13:41,571
That's a nice story.

225
00:13:41,654 --> 00:13:43,906
It's not just a story, Merida.

226
00:13:43,990 --> 00:13:47,076
Legends are lessons.
They ring with truths.

227
00:13:47,118 --> 00:13:48,578
Och, Mum.

228
00:13:48,661 --> 00:13:50,872
I would advise you
to make your peace with this.

229
00:13:50,913 --> 00:13:52,749
The clans are coming
to present their suitors.

230
00:13:52,832 --> 00:13:55,168
- It's not fair.
- Och, Merida.

231
00:13:55,251 --> 00:13:58,004
It's marriage.
It's not the end of the world.

232
00:13:59,088 --> 00:14:00,089
(SIGHS IN DISBELIEF)

233
00:14:02,050 --> 00:14:04,052
(ELINOR MUTTERING)

234
00:14:06,763 --> 00:14:09,474
- FERGUS: You're muttering.
- I don't mutter.

235
00:14:10,099 --> 00:14:13,394
Aye, you do. You mutter, lass,
when something's troubling you.

236
00:14:13,644 --> 00:14:15,730
I blame you. Stubbornness.

237
00:14:15,772 --> 00:14:17,467
It's entirely from your side of the family.

238
00:14:17,482 --> 00:14:20,360
(LAUGHS)
I take it the talk didn't go too well, then?

239
00:14:20,943 --> 00:14:22,945
Och, I don't know what to do.

240
00:14:23,029 --> 00:14:26,074
- Speak to her, dear.
- I do speak to her.

241
00:14:26,115 --> 00:14:29,410
- She just doesn't listen.
- Come on, now.

242
00:14:29,660 --> 00:14:32,038
Pretend I'm Merida. Speak to me.

243
00:14:32,121 --> 00:14:34,082
What would you say?

244
00:14:34,123 --> 00:14:36,626
Och... I can't do this.

245
00:14:36,709 --> 00:14:38,294
Sure you can.

246
00:14:38,378 --> 00:14:40,963
There, there. That's my queen.

247
00:14:41,047 --> 00:14:43,007
Right, here we go.

248
00:14:43,091 --> 00:14:44,801
"I don't want to get married.

249
00:14:44,884 --> 00:14:47,345
"I want to stay single
and let my hair flow in the wind

250
00:14:47,428 --> 00:14:51,349
"as I ride through the glen
firing arrows into the sunset."

251
00:14:54,310 --> 00:14:56,687
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

252
00:14:56,771 --> 00:15:01,776
Merida, all this work,
all the time spent preparing you,

253
00:15:01,818 --> 00:15:05,446
schooling you,
giving you everything we never had.

254
00:15:05,696 --> 00:15:09,158
I ask you, what do you expect us to do?

255
00:15:09,242 --> 00:15:12,328
Call off the gathering.
Would that kill them?

256
00:15:12,412 --> 00:15:13,746
You're the queen.

257
00:15:13,830 --> 00:15:17,166
You can just tell the lords
the princess is not ready for this.

258
00:15:17,208 --> 00:15:20,878
In fact, she might not ever be ready
for this, so that's that.

259
00:15:20,962 --> 00:15:25,007
Good day to you. We'll expect your
declarations of war in the morning.

260
00:15:25,091 --> 00:15:28,803
I understand this must all seem unfair.

261
00:15:28,845 --> 00:15:31,180
Even I had reservations
when I faced betrothal.

262
00:15:31,222 --> 00:15:34,725
But we can't just run away
from who we are.

263
00:15:34,809 --> 00:15:37,311
I don't want my life to be over.

264
00:15:37,353 --> 00:15:38,771
I want my freedom!

265
00:15:38,855 --> 00:15:42,108
But are you willing to pay the price
your freedom will cost?

266
00:15:42,191 --> 00:15:44,318
I'm not doing any of this to hurt you.

267
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:49,907
If you could just try to see what I do,
I do out of love.

268
00:15:49,991 --> 00:15:52,952
But it's my life, it's... (SIGHS)

269
00:15:53,369 --> 00:15:55,121
I'm just not ready.

270
00:15:55,204 --> 00:15:57,081
I think you'd see, if you could just...

271
00:15:57,165 --> 00:16:00,209
I think I could make you understand
if you would just...

272
00:16:00,293 --> 00:16:01,878
- ...listen.
- ...listen.

273
00:16:01,961 --> 00:16:03,296
(WHINNIES)

274
00:16:05,214 --> 00:16:08,384
I swear, Angus,
this isn't going to happen.

275
00:16:09,385 --> 00:16:11,012
Not if I have any say in it.

276
00:16:12,930 --> 00:16:15,558
- (EXERTIVE GRUNTING)
- (DRUMS POUNDING)

277
00:16:17,810 --> 00:16:19,145
(MEN STRAINING)

278
00:16:23,149 --> 00:16:25,151
(DRUMS BEATING RHYTHMICALLY)

279
00:16:27,737 --> 00:16:29,322
MacGuffin!

280
00:16:29,405 --> 00:16:30,907
MEN: MacGuffin!

281
00:16:33,826 --> 00:16:35,828
- Dingwall!
- MEN: Dingwall!

282
00:16:37,538 --> 00:16:40,458
- Macintosh!
- MEN: Macintosh!

283
00:16:46,255 --> 00:16:48,257
Ooh! Aah!

284
00:16:48,841 --> 00:16:49,842
Oh.

285
00:16:51,135 --> 00:16:52,136
(SIGHS)

286
00:16:52,428 --> 00:16:53,429
(GRUNTS)

287
00:16:53,471 --> 00:16:56,933
You look absolutely beautiful.

288
00:16:57,016 --> 00:16:58,309
I can't breathe.

289
00:16:58,392 --> 00:17:00,394
Och, shush! Give us a turn.

290
00:17:01,854 --> 00:17:04,148
(GROANS) I can't move.

291
00:17:04,232 --> 00:17:06,275
It's too tight.

292
00:17:06,359 --> 00:17:09,111
- (STRAINS)
- It's perfect.

293
00:17:09,195 --> 00:17:11,113
(GROANS)

294
00:17:11,781 --> 00:17:13,449
(STRAINS)

295
00:17:21,499 --> 00:17:24,043
- Merida?
- Mum?

296
00:17:26,963 --> 00:17:28,965
Just...

297
00:17:31,592 --> 00:17:33,844
Remember to smile.

298
00:17:37,807 --> 00:17:39,809
(SNORING)

299
00:17:42,937 --> 00:17:44,939
(PRINCES LAUGHING)

300
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:49,318
- (CONTINUES SNORING)
- Aye, they're coming.

301
00:17:49,402 --> 00:17:51,696
Places, everyone. Places.

302
00:17:51,779 --> 00:17:53,281
- (PEOPLE CLAMORING)
- (DOGS BARKING)

303
00:17:53,781 --> 00:17:55,783
Oh!

304
00:18:04,250 --> 00:18:06,252
(PRINCES GRUNTING)

305
00:18:06,544 --> 00:18:08,504
(FERGUS CHUCKLES)

306
00:18:08,588 --> 00:18:11,173
I look fine, woman! Leave me be!

307
00:18:11,507 --> 00:18:12,842
GUARD: My Lord!

308
00:18:12,925 --> 00:18:16,178
I want to announce the arrival
of the lords...

309
00:18:16,220 --> 00:18:18,264
- OW!
- Who goes there? Who goes there?

310
00:18:18,347 --> 00:18:20,349
(BAGPIPES PLAYING)

311
00:18:34,989 --> 00:18:36,991
Boy!

312
00:18:37,658 --> 00:18:39,910
(ALL CRY OUT)

313
00:18:39,994 --> 00:18:41,579
(SHOUTING)

314
00:18:45,207 --> 00:18:46,208
(SILENCE)

315
00:18:47,168 --> 00:18:50,087
So, here we are... Er...

316
00:18:50,880 --> 00:18:53,049
- ...the four clans.
- MAN: Aye.

317
00:18:53,132 --> 00:18:55,134
- Er... Gathering...
- Oh.

318
00:18:55,926 --> 00:18:58,054
- ...for...
- (DISCONTENTED MURMURS)

319
00:18:58,137 --> 00:19:01,682
- ...the presentation of the suitors.
- ...the presentation of the suitors.

320
00:19:01,932 --> 00:19:04,477
- (ALL CHEERING)
- FERGUS: Clan Macintosh.

321
00:19:04,560 --> 00:19:06,896
MEN: Macintosh!

322
00:19:06,979 --> 00:19:10,524
Your Majesty,
I present my heir and scion,

323
00:19:10,566 --> 00:19:14,070
who defended our land
from the northern invaders,

324
00:19:14,153 --> 00:19:18,324
and with his own sword, Stab Blooder,

325
00:19:18,407 --> 00:19:20,576
vanquished 1,000 foes.

326
00:19:20,618 --> 00:19:22,620
MEN: Macintosh!

327
00:19:23,871 --> 00:19:25,831
- (SCOFFS)
- FERGUS: Clan MacGuffin!

328
00:19:25,915 --> 00:19:27,583
MEN: MacGuffin!

329
00:19:28,376 --> 00:19:32,588
Good Majesty, I present my eldest son,

330
00:19:32,672 --> 00:19:35,466
who scuttled the Viking longships

331
00:19:35,549 --> 00:19:40,262
and with his bare hands
vanquished 2,000 foes.

332
00:19:40,513 --> 00:19:42,515
MEN: MacGuffin!

333
00:19:45,267 --> 00:19:46,560
Clan Dingwall.

334
00:19:46,602 --> 00:19:48,604
MEN: Dingwall!

335
00:19:49,689 --> 00:19:52,775
I present my only son

336
00:19:54,276 --> 00:19:58,406
who was besieged by 10,000 Romans

337
00:19:58,447 --> 00:20:02,702
and he took out a whole armada
singlehandedly.

338
00:20:02,827 --> 00:20:04,286
With one arm, he was...

339
00:20:05,579 --> 00:20:08,290
With one arm he was steering the ship

340
00:20:08,332 --> 00:20:11,460
and with the other
he held his mighty sword

341
00:20:11,544 --> 00:20:14,296
and struck down a whole attacking fleet.

342
00:20:14,338 --> 00:20:16,716
- MAN: Lies!
- What? I heard that.

343
00:20:16,966 --> 00:20:18,968
- (MEN SNICKERING)
- Go on. Say it to my face.

344
00:20:19,301 --> 00:20:21,971
Or are ye scared, simpering jackanapes,

345
00:20:22,054 --> 00:20:24,348
afraid to muss your pretty hair?

346
00:20:24,432 --> 00:20:27,601
- At least we have hair.
- And all our teeth.

347
00:20:27,643 --> 00:20:30,271
(SPEAKS IN THICK ACCENT)

348
00:20:30,312 --> 00:20:32,064
- MAN: Huh?
- (SHEEP BLEATS)

349
00:20:32,148 --> 00:20:35,651
And we don't hide under bridges,
you grumpy old troll.

350
00:20:35,693 --> 00:20:37,653
(ALL LAUGHING)

351
00:20:39,155 --> 00:20:41,282
You want to laugh, huh?

352
00:20:41,574 --> 00:20:43,492
Wee Dingwall!

353
00:20:44,660 --> 00:20:46,787
(SCREAMS) Get off me!

354
00:20:47,037 --> 00:20:48,414
(LAUGHING)

355
00:20:48,497 --> 00:20:49,498
(PLAYING LIVELY TUNE)

356
00:20:49,582 --> 00:20:50,958
(GROANING)

357
00:20:54,587 --> 00:20:55,588
(SCREAMS)

358
00:20:56,672 --> 00:20:58,507
(YELPS)

359
00:20:58,549 --> 00:21:01,010
Nut 'em! Nut 'em! That's the way to...

360
00:21:03,220 --> 00:21:04,388
All right.

361
00:21:06,307 --> 00:21:07,725
Shut it!

362
00:21:08,350 --> 00:21:09,518
(MUSIC WINDS DOWN)

363
00:21:10,060 --> 00:21:14,774
Now, that's all done.
You've had your go at each other.

364
00:21:15,024 --> 00:21:16,692
Show a little decorum.

365
00:21:17,735 --> 00:21:19,779
And no more fighting.

366
00:21:20,029 --> 00:21:21,280
- (MACE CLANGING)
- (SCREAMS)

367
00:21:21,363 --> 00:21:22,364
(LIVELY TUNE CONTINUES)

368
00:21:23,032 --> 00:21:24,033
(YELLING)

369
00:21:30,539 --> 00:21:32,208
(BATTLE CRY)

370
00:21:34,376 --> 00:21:35,377
OW!

371
00:21:36,504 --> 00:21:37,505
(GROANS)

372
00:21:38,339 --> 00:21:40,132
(SHEEP BLEATS)

373
00:21:40,591 --> 00:21:41,592
(YELLS)

374
00:21:53,103 --> 00:21:55,105
FERGUS: You want a fresh one?

375
00:21:55,356 --> 00:21:57,107
(MUSIC STOPS)

376
00:21:57,191 --> 00:21:59,193
(CLAN CHIEFS WHINING IN PAIN)

377
00:22:01,237 --> 00:22:02,348
FERGUS: Crivens, you're fierce.

378
00:22:02,363 --> 00:22:03,739
I didn't start it. It was...

379
00:22:03,781 --> 00:22:06,450
My lady Queen, I feel terrible.
My humblest apologies.

380
00:22:06,534 --> 00:22:10,120
- We mean no disrespect.
- I'm sorry, love, I didn't... But...

381
00:22:10,204 --> 00:22:12,331
- Yes, dear.
- (CLEARS THROAT)

382
00:22:12,414 --> 00:22:14,208
Now, where were we?

383
00:22:14,250 --> 00:22:17,878
Ah, yes. In accordance with our laws,

384
00:22:18,128 --> 00:22:20,464
by the rights of our heritage,

385
00:22:20,548 --> 00:22:23,801
only the firstborn of each
of the great leaders

386
00:22:23,884 --> 00:22:26,762
- may be presented as champion.
- Firstborn?

387
00:22:26,804 --> 00:22:31,517
And thus compete for the hand
of the Princess of Dun Broch.

388
00:22:32,101 --> 00:22:35,437
To win the fair maiden
they must prove their worth

389
00:22:35,479 --> 00:22:39,650
by feats of strength or arms
in the games.

390
00:22:39,733 --> 00:22:44,405
It is customary that the challenge
be determined by the princess herself.

391
00:22:44,446 --> 00:22:46,156
Archery! Archery.

392
00:22:46,240 --> 00:22:47,449
(ALL MURMURING)

393
00:22:48,617 --> 00:22:52,413
I choose archery.

394
00:22:53,163 --> 00:22:56,333
- Let the games begin!
- (ALL CHEERING)

395
00:23:05,843 --> 00:23:08,304
(GRUNTING)
(YELLS)

396
00:23:12,224 --> 00:23:13,267
(SCREAMS)

397
00:23:13,309 --> 00:23:14,310
(GRUNTING)

398
00:23:16,645 --> 00:23:18,230
Pull!

399
00:23:18,856 --> 00:23:20,691
- Pull!
- (MEN CRYING OUT IN SURPRISE)

400
00:23:20,816 --> 00:23:22,484
(LIVELY BAGPIPES PLAYING)

401
00:23:28,407 --> 00:23:30,409
- (MAN ROARING)
- (CHILDREN SCREAMING)

402
00:23:33,787 --> 00:23:35,789
(MOOING AND BARKING)

403
00:23:37,416 --> 00:23:39,168
- I'll just take one.
- Ooh!

404
00:23:40,419 --> 00:23:42,421
PRINCE: Ooh!

405
00:23:43,964 --> 00:23:45,549
Oh!

406
00:23:45,633 --> 00:23:49,178
Now, I have told you,
you're not allowed... Oh!

407
00:23:50,262 --> 00:23:51,680
- Oh!
- Argh!

408
00:23:52,264 --> 00:23:53,891
- (PRINCES GIGGLING)
- Oh!

409
00:23:56,936 --> 00:23:58,854
(SHEEP BLEATING)

410
00:24:01,732 --> 00:24:03,734
(HORN SOUNDING)

411
00:24:05,736 --> 00:24:08,489
(DOGS HOWL)

412
00:24:08,614 --> 00:24:10,282
(CROWD CHEERING)

413
00:24:10,658 --> 00:24:12,034
It's time!

414
00:24:14,703 --> 00:24:17,957
- Archers, to your marks!
- Aye, archers, to your marks.

415
00:24:18,207 --> 00:24:20,876
And may the lucky arrow find its target.

416
00:24:20,960 --> 00:24:22,586
(FERGUS CHUCKLES)

417
00:24:26,882 --> 00:24:28,884
(EXCITED SQUEALING)

418
00:24:31,220 --> 00:24:32,930
Oi! Get on with it.

419
00:24:39,770 --> 00:24:41,230
CROWD: Ooh. (LAUGHS)

420
00:24:41,271 --> 00:24:42,564
(GROANS)

421
00:24:43,357 --> 00:24:46,568
- Och!
- I bet he wishes he was tossing cabers.

422
00:24:46,610 --> 00:24:49,571
- Or holding up bridges. (LAUGHS)
- Shh!

423
00:24:51,907 --> 00:24:53,659
(GIRLS SQUEAL)

424
00:24:54,618 --> 00:24:55,661
CROWD: AW...

425
00:24:55,744 --> 00:24:56,912
(YELLS ANGRILY)

426
00:24:56,996 --> 00:25:00,416
At least you hit the target, son.

427
00:25:00,457 --> 00:25:01,917
(CONTINUES YELLING)

428
00:25:02,001 --> 00:25:03,794
Oh, that's attractive.

429
00:25:03,877 --> 00:25:05,879
(CONTINUES WAILING)

430
00:25:07,589 --> 00:25:09,717
- MAN: I got it!
- Good arm.

431
00:25:09,758 --> 00:25:12,886
And such lovely flowing locks.

432
00:25:12,928 --> 00:25:14,555
- Fergus.
- What?

433
00:25:16,724 --> 00:25:17,933
(LAUGHTER)

434
00:25:17,975 --> 00:25:18,976
(GASPS)

435
00:25:23,689 --> 00:25:25,441
Oh, wee lamb.

436
00:25:30,946 --> 00:25:33,615
Oh, come on! Shoot, boy!

437
00:25:34,825 --> 00:25:36,827
- (CROWD CHEERING)
- (LAUGHS IN TRIUMPH)

438
00:25:36,910 --> 00:25:38,787
Well done, lad! Well done.

439
00:25:38,829 --> 00:25:40,831
(STARTS SINGING)

440
00:25:42,291 --> 00:25:44,460
- Feast your eyes!
- (CHIEFS SCREAM)

441
00:25:45,294 --> 00:25:48,047
- That's my boy. (LAUGHS)
- (GAGGING)

442
00:25:48,297 --> 00:25:51,800
Well, that's just grand now, isn't it?

443
00:25:51,842 --> 00:25:54,636
- Guess who's coming to dinner?
- Fergus.

444
00:25:54,678 --> 00:25:57,806
By the way, hope you don't mind
being called Lady Ding...

445
00:25:57,848 --> 00:25:59,850
(WHINES)

446
00:26:04,980 --> 00:26:07,649
- (CROWD GASPS)
- I am Merida.

447
00:26:07,691 --> 00:26:10,944
Firstborn descendant of
Clan Dun Broch.

448
00:26:10,986 --> 00:26:14,490
And I'll be shooting for my own hand.

449
00:26:14,573 --> 00:26:15,699
- Oh!
- (CROWD MURMURING)

450
00:26:16,658 --> 00:26:19,036
What are you doing?

451
00:26:21,789 --> 00:26:23,749
Merida!

452
00:26:23,832 --> 00:26:25,709
Curse this dress!

453
00:26:26,085 --> 00:26:28,087
(SHOCKED GASPS)

454
00:26:31,840 --> 00:26:32,883
(CROWD GASPS IN AWE)

455
00:26:33,008 --> 00:26:34,551
Merida, stop this!

456
00:26:38,847 --> 00:26:41,683
Don't you dare loose another arrow.

457
00:26:48,690 --> 00:26:49,775
(EXHALES)

458
00:26:50,943 --> 00:26:53,112
Merida, I forbid it.

459
00:27:23,892 --> 00:27:26,562
Michty me!
I've just about had enough of you, lass!

460
00:27:26,603 --> 00:27:29,314
- You're the one that wants me to...
- You embarrassed them.

461
00:27:29,398 --> 00:27:31,233
- You embarrassed me.
- I followed the rules.

462
00:27:31,316 --> 00:27:33,235
You don't know what you've done!

463
00:27:33,277 --> 00:27:35,931
- Just don't care how I...
- It'll be fire and sword if it's not set right.

464
00:27:35,946 --> 00:27:38,490
- Just listen!
- I am the Queen!

465
00:27:38,574 --> 00:27:40,117
You listen to me!

466
00:27:40,200 --> 00:27:42,494
Ugh! This is so unfair!

467
00:27:42,578 --> 00:27:44,288
Ha! Unfair?

468
00:27:44,371 --> 00:27:46,415
You're never there for me.

469
00:27:46,498 --> 00:27:49,168
This whole marriage is what you want.

470
00:27:49,251 --> 00:27:52,421
Do you ever bother
to ask what I want? No.

471
00:27:52,504 --> 00:27:55,340
You walk around telling me what to do,
what not to do,

472
00:27:55,424 --> 00:27:57,926
trying to make me be like you.

473
00:27:58,010 --> 00:28:00,304
Well, I'm not going to be like you.

474
00:28:00,387 --> 00:28:02,097
Oh, you're acting like a child.

475
00:28:02,139 --> 00:28:04,975
And you're a beast.

476
00:28:05,058 --> 00:28:06,977
- That's what you are!
- Oh, Merida.

477
00:28:07,060 --> 00:28:09,438
- I'll never be like you.
- No, stop that!

478
00:28:09,479 --> 00:28:12,482
- I'd rather die than be like you!
- (GASPS)

479
00:28:17,112 --> 00:28:19,615
Merida, you are a princess,

480
00:28:19,656 --> 00:28:22,451
- and I expect you to act like one.
- Mum!

481
00:28:23,994 --> 00:28:25,162
Oh!

482
00:28:29,791 --> 00:28:30,792
(WEEPS)

483
00:28:30,876 --> 00:28:32,878
ELINOR: Merida!

484
00:28:33,879 --> 00:28:35,380
Merida!

485
00:28:36,298 --> 00:28:38,258
Oh, dear.

486
00:28:38,300 --> 00:28:40,135
Ah!

487
00:28:42,012 --> 00:28:44,598
Oh, no. What have I done?

488
00:28:46,141 --> 00:28:47,559
Oh.

489
00:28:48,227 --> 00:28:50,229
(SOBBING)

490
00:28:55,317 --> 00:28:57,319
(SOBBING)

491
00:29:13,961 --> 00:29:16,255
Oh! Oh! Oh!

492
00:29:16,922 --> 00:29:17,923
(WHINNIES)

493
00:29:18,507 --> 00:29:20,592
Whoa!

494
00:29:20,676 --> 00:29:23,053
(8088) Angus!

495
00:29:23,595 --> 00:29:26,098
(WHINNIES AND SNORTS)

496
00:29:35,023 --> 00:29:37,025
(ANGUS WHINNIES)

497
00:29:48,161 --> 00:29:50,205
(WISP CALLS)

498
00:29:58,505 --> 00:30:01,049
(WISP CALLS)

499
00:30:09,391 --> 00:30:12,394
- (WHISPERS) Come on, Angus.
- (ANGUS NICKERS)

500
00:30:12,477 --> 00:30:13,687
Angus!

501
00:30:13,729 --> 00:30:15,314
(NICKERS)

502
00:30:15,397 --> 00:30:17,149
(SIGHS)

503
00:30:17,733 --> 00:30:19,735
(WISPS CALL)

504
00:30:21,403 --> 00:30:23,238
(ANGUS NEIGHS)

505
00:30:24,406 --> 00:30:26,533
(WISP CALLS)

506
00:30:30,370 --> 00:30:31,496
(WHINNYING)

507
00:30:55,896 --> 00:30:57,898
(WISP CALLS)

508
00:31:02,569 --> 00:31:05,030
Why would the wisps lead me here?

509
00:31:13,747 --> 00:31:15,749
(BELL TINKLES)

510
00:31:16,500 --> 00:31:17,584
Uh...

511
00:31:20,337 --> 00:31:22,339
(WOOD GENTLY TAPPING)

512
00:31:30,180 --> 00:31:32,140
Oh, look around.

513
00:31:32,224 --> 00:31:34,393
You holler if you see anything you like.

514
00:31:34,476 --> 00:31:36,812
Everything is half off.

515
00:31:37,312 --> 00:31:38,355
Uh...

516
00:31:42,192 --> 00:31:45,278
- Who are you?
- Just a humble woodcarver.

517
00:31:45,320 --> 00:31:46,822
Um...

518
00:31:47,114 --> 00:31:49,658
I don't understand... (GASPS)

519
00:31:49,699 --> 00:31:51,827
- See anything you like?
- Uh...

520
00:31:52,119 --> 00:31:56,206
Perhaps a touch of whimsy
to brighten any dank chamber?

521
00:31:56,289 --> 00:31:58,708
But the will-o'-the-wisps, they...

522
00:31:58,792 --> 00:32:00,794
Oh! This is one of a kind!

523
00:32:01,169 --> 00:32:02,838
I'll make you a deal for this rare prize.

524
00:32:05,173 --> 00:32:06,591
- Your broom!
- Oh! (SNAPS)

525
00:32:07,884 --> 00:32:10,887
- It was sweeping by itself.
- That's ridiculous.

526
00:32:11,179 --> 00:32:13,682
Wood cannot be imbued
with magical properties.

527
00:32:13,765 --> 00:32:17,269
I should know. I'm a wit... Whittler.

528
00:32:17,352 --> 00:32:19,146
Of wood.

529
00:32:19,187 --> 00:32:24,484
Oh, how about this conversation starter?
It's made of yew wood.

530
00:32:24,526 --> 00:32:26,862
- (GENTLE CLATTERING)
- Tough as stone.

531
00:32:26,945 --> 00:32:28,363
Oh, ah, ah, ah, ah!

532
00:32:28,405 --> 00:32:30,490
That's stuffed. (LAUGHS)

533
00:32:30,532 --> 00:32:33,827
- Staring is rude.
- (GASPS) Ooh! The crow's talking!

534
00:32:33,869 --> 00:32:35,162
That's not all I can do.

535
00:32:35,203 --> 00:32:37,497
<i>La-la la-la la-la</i>

536
00:32:37,539 --> 00:32:39,416
(SINGS HIGH NOTES)
(SNAPS)

537
00:32:41,710 --> 00:32:43,336
(SQUAWKS)

538
00:32:43,879 --> 00:32:46,840
- You're a witch!
- Woodcarver.

539
00:32:46,882 --> 00:32:49,217
That's why the wisps led me here.

540
00:32:49,718 --> 00:32:51,761
- Woodcarver!
- You'll change my fate!

541
00:32:51,845 --> 00:32:54,639
- Woodcarver!
- You see, it's my mother.

542
00:32:54,723 --> 00:32:57,809
I'm not a witch!
Too many unsatisfied customers.

543
00:33:00,228 --> 00:33:05,192
If you're not going to buy anything,
get out. (SNAPS)

544
00:33:05,567 --> 00:33:08,403
- No! The wisps led me here!
- I don't care!

545
00:33:09,571 --> 00:33:14,159
- Get out! Shoo! Get! Be gone with you!
- I'll buy it all.

546
00:33:14,868 --> 00:33:17,454
- What? What was that?
- Every carving.

547
00:33:17,537 --> 00:33:19,247
Well... (STAMMERING)

548
00:33:19,289 --> 00:33:23,585
(LAUGHS) And how are you going
to pay for that, sweetie?

549
00:33:23,668 --> 00:33:26,338
- With this.
- W...

550
00:33:28,924 --> 00:33:31,843
Oh, my, that's lovely, that is.

551
00:33:31,927 --> 00:33:33,261
That would set us up for months.

552
00:33:33,386 --> 00:33:34,386
(CLATTERING)

553
00:33:35,305 --> 00:33:36,723
- MERIDA: Ah, ah, ah.
- (GASPS)

554
00:33:36,765 --> 00:33:42,604
- Every carving and one spell.
- (SQUAWKS)

555
00:33:43,355 --> 00:33:46,316
Are you sure
you know what you're doing?

556
00:33:46,399 --> 00:33:49,945
I want a spell to change my mum.

557
00:33:50,195 --> 00:33:52,489
That'll change my fate.

558
00:33:52,572 --> 00:33:53,865
Hmm... Done!

559
00:33:55,283 --> 00:33:56,785
- (CHUCKLES)
- Where are you going?

560
00:33:56,826 --> 00:33:57,869
(SNAPS)

561
00:33:57,953 --> 00:33:59,579
- (SQUAWKING)
- There.

562
00:33:59,621 --> 00:34:00,956
What are you doing?

563
00:34:01,373 --> 00:34:03,959
You never conjure where you carve.

564
00:34:04,251 --> 00:34:05,627
Very important.

565
00:34:09,381 --> 00:34:11,758
WITCH: The last time I did this
was for a prince.

566
00:34:11,841 --> 00:34:13,385
- (CLAPS)
- (CAULDRON IGNITES)

567
00:34:13,468 --> 00:34:15,762
Easy on the eyes. Tight pants.

568
00:34:15,804 --> 00:34:19,474
He demanded I give him
the strength of ten men.

569
00:34:19,516 --> 00:34:22,769
And he gave me this for a spell.

570
00:34:23,562 --> 00:34:25,522
A spell that would change his fate.

571
00:34:27,440 --> 00:34:28,858
And did he get what he was after?

572
00:34:28,942 --> 00:34:30,610
(LAUGHS) Yes.

573
00:34:30,652 --> 00:34:34,781
And made off with an especially
attractive mahogany cheese board.

574
00:34:34,823 --> 00:34:37,617
Now, what do I need? Oh!

575
00:34:37,659 --> 00:34:39,703
- Just a little bit of this.
- (THUNDER RUMBLING)

576
00:34:39,786 --> 00:34:40,787
Ah. (CHUCKLES)

577
00:34:40,870 --> 00:34:41,871
Hoo!

578
00:34:42,914 --> 00:34:45,417
(SQUAWKING)

579
00:34:45,500 --> 00:34:47,836
Tee-tee-tee-tee. Whoosh.

580
00:34:47,919 --> 00:34:49,671
That'll do.

581
00:34:54,009 --> 00:34:56,011
(HUMS HAPPILY)

582
00:34:57,470 --> 00:34:59,681
- (SQUAWKS)
- Mi-mi-mi-mi-mi-mi-mi.

583
00:35:02,892 --> 00:35:03,893
(BANG)

584
00:35:03,977 --> 00:35:05,770
(PANICKED WHINNYING)

585
00:35:07,397 --> 00:35:13,528
And now let's see. What have we here?

586
00:35:16,573 --> 00:35:18,366
(GASPS) Oh!

587
00:35:19,409 --> 00:35:20,493
- Hey!
- (SQUAWKS)

588
00:35:21,536 --> 00:35:23,371
Uh, a cake?

589
00:35:23,455 --> 00:35:26,458
- You don't want it?
- Yes! I want it.

590
00:35:27,000 --> 00:35:31,087
You're sure if I give this to my mum,

591
00:35:31,379 --> 00:35:33,089
it will change my fate?

592
00:35:33,381 --> 00:35:34,924
Oh. (CHUCKLES)

593
00:35:35,008 --> 00:35:38,303
Trust me. It'll do the trick, dearie.

594
00:35:38,970 --> 00:35:43,850
Expect delivery of your purchase
within a fortnight.

595
00:35:43,892 --> 00:35:45,894
Ooh! Ooh...

596
00:35:46,770 --> 00:35:48,980
What was that thing about the spell?

597
00:35:49,731 --> 00:35:52,651
Did you say something about

598
00:35:53,610 --> 00:35:55,737
the spell?

599
00:35:58,740 --> 00:36:03,745
<i>Mor'du, Mor'du, now the time has
come for all of us to slaughter you</i>

600
00:36:04,496 --> 00:36:05,497
ALL: Hooray!

601
00:36:05,580 --> 00:36:06,998
<i>Mor'du, Mor'du...</i>

602
00:36:08,583 --> 00:36:10,585
(DISTANT SINGING)

603
00:36:25,767 --> 00:36:27,769
- ELINOR: Merida.
- Mum!

604
00:36:27,852 --> 00:36:29,688
Ooh, uh... I, uh...

605
00:36:29,771 --> 00:36:32,899
- Oh, I've been worried sick.
- You... You were?

606
00:36:32,941 --> 00:36:36,486
I didn't know where you'd gone
or when you'd come back.

607
00:36:36,569 --> 00:36:39,447
I didn't know what to think.
Oh, look at your dress.

608
00:36:39,531 --> 00:36:42,450
Oh. Angus threw me. But I'm not hurt.

609
00:36:42,492 --> 00:36:46,621
Well, you're home now,
so that's the end of it.

610
00:36:47,622 --> 00:36:50,959
- Honestly?
- I've pacified the lords for now.

611
00:36:51,042 --> 00:36:54,003
Your father's out there
"entertaining" them.

612
00:36:54,087 --> 00:36:55,922
♪ <i>Come taste my blade, you manky bear</i> ♪

613
00:36:55,964 --> 00:36:57,632
♪ <i>For gobbling up my leg</i> ♪

614
00:36:58,049 --> 00:37:01,803
♪ <i>I'll hunt you, then I'll skin you, ♪
♪ hang your noggin on a peg...</i> ♪

615
00:37:01,845 --> 00:37:03,054
(CHEERING)

616
00:37:04,139 --> 00:37:07,976
Of course, we both know
a decision still has to be made.

617
00:37:11,938 --> 00:37:14,774
- What's this?
- It's a peace offering.

618
00:37:14,816 --> 00:37:17,986
I made it. For you. Special.

619
00:37:18,069 --> 00:37:20,947
You made this for me?

620
00:37:22,657 --> 00:37:23,700
Mm.

621
00:37:26,619 --> 00:37:29,414
Oh. Interesting flavor.

622
00:37:29,497 --> 00:37:32,500
- How do you feel?
- What... What is that?

623
00:37:32,542 --> 00:37:34,169
- Different?
- Mm...

624
00:37:34,419 --> 00:37:37,714
Tart and, um, (GULPS) gamy.

625
00:37:37,797 --> 00:37:41,509
Have you changed your mind at all
about the marriage and all that?

626
00:37:42,510 --> 00:37:44,012
Oh, that's better.

627
00:37:44,095 --> 00:37:46,598
Now, why don't we go
upstairs to the lords

628
00:37:46,681 --> 00:37:49,601
and put this whole kerfuffle to rest?

629
00:37:49,684 --> 00:37:51,019
Hm?

630
00:37:55,482 --> 00:37:56,900
(CELTIC FLUTE MUSIC PLAYING)

631
00:37:57,692 --> 00:37:58,735
Ooh.

632
00:37:58,818 --> 00:38:01,654
- Mother?
- I'm woozy suddenly.

633
00:38:01,696 --> 00:38:04,157
My head's spinning like atop. Ooh!

634
00:38:04,199 --> 00:38:07,994
- Mum!
- Oh, suddenly I'm not so well.

635
00:38:08,036 --> 00:38:11,873
Er... How... How do you feel
about the marriage now?

636
00:38:11,956 --> 00:38:15,001
Merida! Oh, just take me to my room.

637
00:38:15,043 --> 00:38:17,670
FERGUS: All right, that's fine.
That's just fine.

638
00:38:17,712 --> 00:38:21,549
A little to the left. That's good.
A wee bit to the left. That's good.

639
00:38:21,633 --> 00:38:23,092
It's good enough.

640
00:38:23,176 --> 00:38:25,736
Now, clear out of there, boys.
I don't want you to spoil my shot.

641
00:38:26,221 --> 00:38:28,014
- What? (CLEARS THROAT)
- My lady Queen.

642
00:38:28,056 --> 00:38:31,017
We've been waiting patiently.

643
00:38:31,059 --> 00:38:36,064
Milords, I am out of sorts
at the moment.

644
00:38:36,147 --> 00:38:39,943
But you shall have your answer.
(BURPS)

645
00:38:40,026 --> 00:38:41,528
- Oh!
- Eh?

646
00:38:41,569 --> 00:38:43,571
Presently.

647
00:38:43,613 --> 00:38:46,574
Now, if you'll (GROANS) excuse us.

648
00:38:48,243 --> 00:38:49,869
- (ALL CHEERING)
- FERGUS: Elinor, look!

649
00:38:49,911 --> 00:38:51,913
It's Mor'du! (LAUGHS)

650
00:38:53,581 --> 00:38:55,458
Elinor? Are you all right, dear?

651
00:38:55,542 --> 00:38:57,418
Fine. I'm fine.

652
00:38:57,460 --> 00:38:59,754
Go about avenging your leg. Oh...

653
00:38:59,796 --> 00:39:01,881
Aye. You heard her, lads.

654
00:39:01,923 --> 00:39:06,052
I dream about the perfect way
to make this devil die.

655
00:39:06,094 --> 00:39:07,428
(ALL CHEERING)

656
00:39:09,472 --> 00:39:13,434
Just take all the time you need
to getting yourself right, Mum.

657
00:39:13,518 --> 00:39:17,480
Then maybe in a bit you might have
something new to say on the marriage.

658
00:39:17,564 --> 00:39:19,983
What was in that cake?

659
00:39:20,066 --> 00:39:21,651
(SCOFFS) Cake.

660
00:39:21,776 --> 00:39:23,444
(COUGHS)
(GROANS)

661
00:39:23,862 --> 00:39:25,071
Mum?

662
00:39:25,113 --> 00:39:27,782
So I'll just tell them
the wedding's off, then?

663
00:39:27,866 --> 00:39:29,868
(ELINOR GROANING)

664
00:39:32,871 --> 00:39:34,873
Mum?

665
00:39:38,459 --> 00:39:40,461
(DEEP GROANING)

666
00:39:50,889 --> 00:39:52,640
(GASPS)

667
00:39:55,518 --> 00:39:57,812
(SCREAMS)

668
00:39:58,938 --> 00:40:00,189
(LOW GROWLING)

669
00:40:01,900 --> 00:40:02,984
Bear!

670
00:40:04,027 --> 00:40:05,695
(WHINES)

671
00:40:05,778 --> 00:40:07,780
(FRIGHTENED GROWL)

672
00:40:07,864 --> 00:40:09,115
(PANTING)

673
00:40:11,701 --> 00:40:13,786
- (GROWLS)
- (SCREAMS)

674
00:40:22,211 --> 00:40:24,923
(SURPRISED ROARING)

675
00:40:26,799 --> 00:40:27,800
- (GROANS)
- Oh!

676
00:40:37,268 --> 00:40:38,811
Mum?

677
00:40:40,563 --> 00:40:43,816
You're... You're a bear!

678
00:40:44,859 --> 00:40:45,860
(GROANS)

679
00:40:45,944 --> 00:40:47,320
Why a bear?

680
00:40:47,570 --> 00:40:51,574
Oh, that scaffy witch
gave me a gammy spell.

681
00:40:53,618 --> 00:40:54,953
It's not my fault.

682
00:40:55,036 --> 00:40:57,038
I didn't ask her
to change you into a bear.

683
00:40:57,080 --> 00:41:01,709
I just wanted her to change you.

684
00:41:03,086 --> 00:41:04,796
(ROARS)

685
00:41:05,797 --> 00:41:07,715
(ALL CHEERING)

686
00:41:07,757 --> 00:41:10,218
- Shh. Did you hear that? (SNIFFS)
- (MUSIC STOPS)

687
00:41:10,301 --> 00:41:12,553
Something's not right.

688
00:41:12,637 --> 00:41:14,973
(ANXIOUS WHINING)

689
00:41:15,890 --> 00:41:19,227
There's no point in having a go at me.
The witch is to blame.

690
00:41:19,268 --> 00:41:21,646
Goggly old hag.

691
00:41:22,355 --> 00:41:24,816
Eyes all over the place.

692
00:41:25,608 --> 00:41:27,902
- Unbelievable.
- (GROANING)

693
00:41:29,070 --> 00:41:31,698
- I'll get her to fix this.
- (SIGHS)

694
00:41:31,739 --> 00:41:34,500
MERIDA: Why do I always get blamed
for everything? It's just not fair.

695
00:41:35,743 --> 00:41:37,745
(SNIFFING)

696
00:41:37,829 --> 00:41:40,081
Everybody, follow me.

697
00:41:40,164 --> 00:41:42,166
And keep a sharp eye.

698
00:41:43,793 --> 00:41:46,546
Here we go.
Another hunt through the castle.

699
00:41:46,587 --> 00:41:48,256
But we haven't had dessert yet.

700
00:41:48,381 --> 00:41:51,759
(SPEAKS IN THICK ACCENT)

701
00:41:53,594 --> 00:41:55,596
(LAUGHS) I have no idea.

702
00:41:56,597 --> 00:41:59,225
MERIDA: Mum, you can't go out there.

703
00:42:00,268 --> 00:42:02,645
Mum! Wait!

704
00:42:04,272 --> 00:42:08,151
What are you doing?
Dad. The Bear King?

705
00:42:08,234 --> 00:42:10,403
If he so much as sees you, you're dead.

706
00:42:10,653 --> 00:42:14,282
LORD DINGWALL: Another one of
your entertainments to bore us to death!

707
00:42:14,323 --> 00:42:15,935
LORD MACINTOSH:
Oh, and what exactly are we after...

708
00:42:15,950 --> 00:42:16,951
Mum!

709
00:42:17,035 --> 00:42:18,911
LORD MACINTOSH: ...my liege?

710
00:42:18,953 --> 00:42:22,123
LORD MACGUFFIN: Best to humor him.
He is, after all, the King.

711
00:42:22,206 --> 00:42:23,249
(SNIFFING)

712
00:42:26,044 --> 00:42:28,421
He's like a hound with that nose of his.

713
00:42:28,671 --> 00:42:29,797
(LICKS AND SPITS)

714
00:42:29,881 --> 00:42:31,716
Mum, wait.

715
00:42:31,799 --> 00:42:33,217
- We have to...
- (GROANS)

716
00:42:33,301 --> 00:42:35,678
- (CLATTERING)
- Follow me.

717
00:42:35,762 --> 00:42:37,388
Stop.

718
00:42:37,638 --> 00:42:38,681
Stop!

719
00:42:40,016 --> 00:42:41,017
(GASPS)

720
00:42:42,018 --> 00:42:44,187
You're covered with fur.

721
00:42:44,270 --> 00:42:45,980
You're not naked.

722
00:42:46,022 --> 00:42:47,982
It's not like anyone's gonna see you.

723
00:42:52,987 --> 00:42:54,405
(SCREAMS)

724
00:42:55,323 --> 00:42:56,866
Now you've done it.

725
00:42:56,949 --> 00:42:58,701
(SCREAMS)

726
00:42:59,285 --> 00:43:01,079
Maudie!

727
00:43:01,162 --> 00:43:03,873
- (STUTTERING)
- Just calm down, lass. What is it?

728
00:43:03,956 --> 00:43:06,125
- (STUTTERING)
- Spit it out, Maudie!

729
00:43:06,167 --> 00:43:08,002
(SHOUTING) A bear!

730
00:43:08,086 --> 00:43:09,712
I knew it! (YELLS)

731
00:43:09,796 --> 00:43:10,922
(ALL SHOUTING)

732
00:43:11,005 --> 00:43:12,840
Would you just listen to me?

733
00:43:12,882 --> 00:43:15,760
- We can't go this way. You'll be seen.
- (MEN YELLING)

734
00:43:15,843 --> 00:43:17,136
Quick! This way!

735
00:43:19,514 --> 00:43:20,515
Mum?

736
00:43:26,771 --> 00:43:28,523
(WHIMPERS)

737
00:43:33,945 --> 00:43:35,071
(ALL GASP)

738
00:43:36,739 --> 00:43:38,449
(SOFTLY) Mum? Oh!

739
00:43:38,699 --> 00:43:40,701
(MEN SHOUTING)

740
00:43:43,996 --> 00:43:46,124
- Oh!
- (ELINOR WHINING)

741
00:43:55,133 --> 00:43:56,175
Hm?

742
00:43:57,260 --> 00:44:00,429
A witch turned Mum into a bear.
It's not my fault.

743
00:44:00,513 --> 00:44:02,890
We've got to get out of the castle.
I need your help.

744
00:44:03,432 --> 00:44:05,184
Oh, all right.

745
00:44:05,226 --> 00:44:08,521
You can have my desserts
for two... Three weeks.

746
00:44:10,231 --> 00:44:12,358
Okay. Fine. A year.

747
00:44:18,406 --> 00:44:20,199
- Did you hear that?
- Shh.

748
00:44:20,241 --> 00:44:22,118
(ECHOING ROAR)

749
00:44:24,453 --> 00:44:26,747
(ECHOING ROAR)

750
00:44:27,957 --> 00:44:30,209
- There it goes!
- (MEN SHOUTING)

751
00:44:31,919 --> 00:44:33,406
- (MOCK ROARING CONTINUES)
- FERGUS: Come on, lads!

752
00:44:33,421 --> 00:44:35,256
(YELLS)

753
00:44:37,425 --> 00:44:39,844
- (YELLS)
- (MOCK GROWLING)

754
00:44:41,262 --> 00:44:42,346
There it goes!

755
00:44:43,890 --> 00:44:45,600
(ALL YELLING)

756
00:44:50,938 --> 00:44:52,481
(BIRD CALL)

757
00:44:55,943 --> 00:44:58,279
- Come on, Mum.
- (WHINES)

758
00:44:58,321 --> 00:45:00,239
(CLATTERING)

759
00:45:01,949 --> 00:45:03,269
LORD MACGUFFIN:
Think we should lay a trap?

760
00:45:03,284 --> 00:45:04,994
FERGUS: Try shutting yours!

761
00:45:05,077 --> 00:45:07,079
(ALL ARGUING)

762
00:45:07,121 --> 00:45:08,456
(MOCK GROWLING)

763
00:45:08,539 --> 00:45:10,374
- There he is!
- (MEN SHOUTING)

764
00:45:15,338 --> 00:45:17,089
(ALL SHOUTING)

765
00:45:22,803 --> 00:45:24,472
FERGUS: I'm sure it went this way.

766
00:45:24,555 --> 00:45:26,167
LORD MACGUFFIN:
You can see my house from here.

767
00:45:26,182 --> 00:45:28,142
It must have sprouted wings.

768
00:45:28,184 --> 00:45:31,354
Was carried away by a giant birdy.

769
00:45:31,437 --> 00:45:34,440
- A dragon, perhaps.
- Bear in the castle!

770
00:45:34,482 --> 00:45:36,859
Doesn't make sense.
It cannot open doors.

771
00:45:36,943 --> 00:45:38,819
He's got big giant paws!

772
00:45:38,903 --> 00:45:40,279
Let's just get inside.

773
00:45:40,988 --> 00:45:42,365
(GRUNTING)

774
00:45:42,448 --> 00:45:45,159
- It's locked.
- Dingwall was the last up.

775
00:45:45,243 --> 00:45:47,411
LORD DINGWALL:
I propped it open with a stick.

776
00:45:47,495 --> 00:45:49,163
(MEN GRUMBLING)

777
00:45:53,542 --> 00:45:57,171
HANDMAID: What did you see, Maudie?
Just spit it out, Maudie.

778
00:45:57,255 --> 00:45:59,799
Oh, for goodness' sakes, Maudie,
would you get a grip?

779
00:45:59,840 --> 00:46:00,841
(CLATTERING)

780
00:46:03,177 --> 00:46:05,221
(SCREAMS)

781
00:46:05,304 --> 00:46:07,304
HANDMAID: Maudie, honey, come here!
It's all right!

782
00:46:08,474 --> 00:46:10,017
Come on, Mum. Quick.

783
00:46:10,935 --> 00:46:11,936
(GROANS)

784
00:46:12,019 --> 00:46:13,437
Shh.

785
00:46:19,360 --> 00:46:21,445
(CRASHING AND CLATTERING)

786
00:46:23,030 --> 00:46:25,032
(CLATTERING)

787
00:46:26,284 --> 00:46:27,952
(GIGGLING)

788
00:46:28,244 --> 00:46:29,245
(SNEEZES)

789
00:46:30,079 --> 00:46:31,247
(WHINES)

790
00:46:31,330 --> 00:46:33,165
They'll be fine. Won't you, boys?

791
00:46:33,207 --> 00:46:34,208
(SNIFFS)

792
00:46:34,625 --> 00:46:37,003
Mum, we've got to hurry.

793
00:46:37,044 --> 00:46:38,504
Now, I'll be back soon.

794
00:46:38,546 --> 00:46:41,841
Go on and help yourself
to anything you want, as a reward.

795
00:46:43,634 --> 00:46:45,469
(ALL GASP)

796
00:46:56,063 --> 00:46:58,441
(STRAINING) Oh!

797
00:46:58,524 --> 00:46:59,525
(LORD DINGWALL SIGHS)

798
00:46:59,650 --> 00:47:01,360
Right!

799
00:47:08,492 --> 00:47:10,578
MERIDA: Where are these wisps?

800
00:47:10,619 --> 00:47:13,956
Come out, wisps. Come on out.

801
00:47:15,583 --> 00:47:18,169
Lead me to the witch's cottage.

802
00:47:19,295 --> 00:47:21,297
I'm here!

803
00:47:22,214 --> 00:47:25,801
Fine. Don't come out
now that my mum's watching.

804
00:47:25,885 --> 00:47:26,927
(WHINES)

805
00:47:27,011 --> 00:47:32,016
I was standing right here
and the wisp appeared right there.

806
00:47:32,099 --> 00:47:35,519
Then a whole trail of them
led me off into the forest.

807
00:47:41,609 --> 00:47:45,946
Oh, does she think we're just going
to happen upon the witch's cottage?

808
00:47:46,989 --> 00:47:48,407
(OWLS HOOTING)

809
00:47:54,497 --> 00:47:56,123
(DISTANT HOWLING)

810
00:47:59,960 --> 00:48:02,171
Oh, Mum, I know this place.

811
00:48:02,713 --> 00:48:04,673
The witch's cottage...

812
00:48:05,466 --> 00:48:08,636
It's this way! Come on! Hurry!

813
00:48:18,020 --> 00:48:20,981
I can't believe it. I found it.

814
00:48:21,065 --> 00:48:22,900
(WHINES)

815
00:48:25,528 --> 00:48:28,280
No. She was here.

816
00:48:29,240 --> 00:48:32,410
No, really, she was just here.

817
00:48:32,493 --> 00:48:33,702
(WHINES)

818
00:48:33,994 --> 00:48:35,454
Oh, wait.

819
00:48:40,126 --> 00:48:42,169
- No.
- (BANGS DOOR SHUT)

820
00:48:42,253 --> 00:48:45,673
No, no. No! No!

821
00:48:47,925 --> 00:48:50,010
- (METAL RATTLES)
- Oh.

822
00:48:50,094 --> 00:48:52,346
(RUMBLING)

823
00:48:54,515 --> 00:48:55,599
(DINGING)

824
00:48:58,102 --> 00:49:00,271
(SHRIEKS)

825
00:49:01,188 --> 00:49:03,190
(BUBBLING)

826
00:49:10,614 --> 00:49:13,492
<i>Welcome to the Crafty Carver,</i>

827
00:49:13,534 --> 00:49:17,037
<i>home of bear-themed carvings
and novelties.</i>

828
00:49:17,079 --> 00:49:20,207
<i>I am completely out of stock at this time.</i>

829
00:49:20,291 --> 00:49:25,588
<i>But if you'd like to enquire about
portraits or wedding cake toppers,</i>

830
00:49:25,671 --> 00:49:27,631
<i>pour vial one into the cauldron.</i>

831
00:49:27,715 --> 00:49:30,384
<i>If you'd like the menu in Gaelic, vial two.</i>

832
00:49:30,468 --> 00:49:33,304
<i>If you're that red-haired lass, vial three.</i>

833
00:49:33,387 --> 00:49:35,723
<i>To speak with a live homunculus...</i>

834
00:49:36,390 --> 00:49:40,269
<i>Princess, I'm off to the Wickerman
Festival in Stornoway</i>

835
00:49:40,352 --> 00:49:42,354
<i>and won't be back till spring.</i>

836
00:49:42,396 --> 00:49:46,066
<i>There's one bit I forgot to tell you
about the spell.</i>

837
00:49:46,108 --> 00:49:49,987
<i>By the second sunrise,
your spell will be permanent,</i>

838
00:49:50,070 --> 00:49:54,408
- (GASPS)
<i>- Unless you remember these words.</i>

839
00:49:55,409 --> 00:49:57,495
<i>Fate be changed,</i>

840
00:49:57,578 --> 00:49:59,538
<i>look inside,</i>

841
00:49:59,580 --> 00:50:01,499
<i>mend the bond</i>

842
00:50:01,582 --> 00:50:03,626
<i>torn by pride.</i>

843
00:50:03,709 --> 00:50:07,755
"Fate be changed... Mend the bond."
What does that mean?

844
00:50:07,838 --> 00:50:09,548
<i>One more time.</i>

845
00:50:09,590 --> 00:50:11,467
<i>Fate be changed,</i>

846
00:50:11,550 --> 00:50:13,594
<i>look inside,</i>

847
00:50:13,677 --> 00:50:15,471
<i>mend the bond</i>

848
00:50:15,554 --> 00:50:18,098
<i>torn by pride.</i>

849
00:50:18,182 --> 00:50:19,558
<i>That's it. Ta-ta.</i>

850
00:50:19,600 --> 00:50:23,479
<i>Oh, and thank you for shopping
at the Crafty Carver.</i>

851
00:50:23,562 --> 00:50:26,232
No. No! Where'd you go?

852
00:50:26,273 --> 00:50:28,776
<i>- Welcome to the Crafty Carver...</i>
- What?

853
00:50:28,859 --> 00:50:31,111
<i>...for</i> all <i>your...</i>
(SPEECH OVERLAPPING)

854
00:50:31,153 --> 00:50:35,449
Maybe there's a book of spells.
Look around. We'll need more vials.

855
00:50:37,326 --> 00:50:40,371
<i>I'm off to the Wickerman Festival
in Stornoway...</i>

856
00:50:40,454 --> 00:50:42,623
(SCRAMBLED MESSAGES)

857
00:50:43,332 --> 00:50:46,377
<i>Thank you for visiting.
Have a lovely day.</i>

858
00:50:46,460 --> 00:50:47,461
(BANG)

859
00:50:52,258 --> 00:50:54,260
(WHINES SOFTLY)

860
00:51:05,104 --> 00:51:07,022
(RAIN PATTERING)

861
00:51:07,106 --> 00:51:08,315
(MERIDA STRAINING)

862
00:51:19,159 --> 00:51:20,286
(ELINOR SIGHS)

863
00:51:23,372 --> 00:51:25,624
We'll sort it out tomorrow.

864
00:51:43,892 --> 00:51:46,020
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

865
00:51:53,944 --> 00:51:55,946
(FAINT SINGING)

866
00:51:59,408 --> 00:52:01,410
(ELINOR SINGING IN GAELIC)

867
00:52:08,334 --> 00:52:10,544
- (CRACK OF THUNDER)
- (SCREAMS)

868
00:52:11,211 --> 00:52:13,255
Oh. (SPEAKS GAELIC)

869
00:52:14,214 --> 00:52:17,301
My brave wee lassie, I'm here.

870
00:52:17,384 --> 00:52:20,387
I'll always be right here.

871
00:52:22,306 --> 00:52:24,308
(CONTINUES SINGING IN GAELIC)

872
00:52:25,934 --> 00:52:27,936
(BOTH SINGING)

873
00:52:39,573 --> 00:52:41,575
(BIRDSONG)

874
00:52:42,618 --> 00:52:44,787
Uh... Good morning.

875
00:52:44,870 --> 00:52:46,830
(MOANS)

876
00:52:46,914 --> 00:52:48,957
So... (CHUCKLES)

877
00:52:49,249 --> 00:52:52,419
- What's all this supposed to be?
- (SIGHS)

878
00:52:52,503 --> 00:52:54,254
Oh.

879
00:52:54,338 --> 00:52:56,507
(MOANS AND GRUNTS)

880
00:52:56,590 --> 00:52:58,258
What?

881
00:52:58,342 --> 00:53:00,678
(HUFFS AND SNORTS)

882
00:53:05,015 --> 00:53:06,934
Sorry. I don't speak bear.

883
00:53:07,017 --> 00:53:08,060
(HUFFS)

884
00:53:12,022 --> 00:53:13,524
Oh.

885
00:53:14,566 --> 00:53:15,567
(MOANS)

886
00:53:18,320 --> 00:53:19,363
Ah!

887
00:53:19,446 --> 00:53:20,614
(GRUNTS IN SURPRISE)

888
00:53:24,535 --> 00:53:25,536
(SLURPS)

889
00:53:27,955 --> 00:53:30,624
- Find those by the creek, did you?
- Mm-hm.

890
00:53:30,708 --> 00:53:32,084
They're nightshade berries.

891
00:53:32,167 --> 00:53:33,919
Mmm.

892
00:53:34,628 --> 00:53:36,255
They're poisonous.

893
00:53:37,965 --> 00:53:38,966
(SPUTTERING)

894
00:53:44,805 --> 00:53:47,850
Where did you get this water?
It has worms.

895
00:53:50,936 --> 00:53:52,813
(GULPS)

896
00:53:53,814 --> 00:53:54,857
(THUDDING)

897
00:53:54,940 --> 00:53:56,692
(BIRDS SQUAWK)

898
00:53:58,694 --> 00:54:01,613
- (GIGGLES) Come on.
- (GROWLS SOFTLY)

899
00:54:09,663 --> 00:54:10,831
Breakfast.

900
00:54:11,498 --> 00:54:12,624
(GRUNTS APPROVINGLY)

901
00:54:12,666 --> 00:54:17,588
Oh, wait. A princess should not
have weapons, in your opinion.

902
00:54:17,713 --> 00:54:19,465
Uh-huh... (GROANS)

903
00:54:19,506 --> 00:54:20,924
There you go.

904
00:54:22,426 --> 00:54:23,844
Go on.

905
00:54:23,927 --> 00:54:25,804
(GROANS)

906
00:54:26,680 --> 00:54:29,349
How do you know you don't like it
if you won't try it?

907
00:54:29,391 --> 00:54:30,684
(WHINES)

908
00:54:39,318 --> 00:54:40,402
(GROANS APPROVINGLY)

909
00:54:44,782 --> 00:54:46,283
Mm.

910
00:54:47,034 --> 00:54:48,035
(MUNCHING LOUDLY)

911
00:54:54,291 --> 00:54:55,751
(GRUNTS)

912
00:54:56,543 --> 00:54:57,920
(BURPS)

913
00:54:58,003 --> 00:54:59,129
(GROANS)

914
00:54:59,213 --> 00:55:01,006
(SLOW SONG PLAYING)

915
00:55:01,048 --> 00:55:05,469
♪ <i>This love it is a distant star</i> ♪

916
00:55:05,552 --> 00:55:09,681
♪ <i>Guiding us home wherever we are</i> ♪

917
00:55:10,641 --> 00:55:14,770
♪ <i>This love it is a burning sun</i> ♪

918
00:55:15,020 --> 00:55:19,316
♪ <i>Shining light on the things ♪
♪ that we've done</i> ♪

919
00:55:20,234 --> 00:55:26,073
♪ <i>I tried to speak to you every day</i> ♪

920
00:55:26,156 --> 00:55:33,080
♪ <i>But each word we spoke ♪
♪ the wind blew away</i> ♪

921
00:55:37,125 --> 00:55:40,420
♪ <i>How did we let it come to this?</i> ♪

922
00:55:41,839 --> 00:55:43,590
♪ <i>What we just tasted...</i> ♪

923
00:55:43,674 --> 00:55:45,592
(MERIDA LAUGHS)

924
00:55:48,011 --> 00:55:53,517
♪ <i>How will it feel when this day is done?</i> ♪

925
00:55:53,851 --> 00:56:00,816
♪ <i>And can we keep ♪
♪ what we've only begun?</i> ♪

926
00:56:01,483 --> 00:56:02,526
(CRIES OUT)

927
00:56:02,609 --> 00:56:08,282
♪ <i>Could these walls ♪
♪ come crumbling down?</i> ♪

928
00:56:09,449 --> 00:56:15,455
♪ <i>I want to feel my feet on the ground</i> ♪

929
00:56:16,415 --> 00:56:21,211
♪ <i>Can we carry this love that we share</i> ♪

930
00:56:22,337 --> 00:56:27,050
♪ <i>Into the open air</i> ♪

931
00:56:29,344 --> 00:56:34,975
♪ <i>Into the open air</i> ♪

932
00:56:37,311 --> 00:56:38,437
Hey!

933
00:56:40,105 --> 00:56:42,482
Where are you going?

934
00:56:48,113 --> 00:56:53,243
♪ <i>This love it is a burning sun</i> ♪

935
00:56:53,493 --> 00:56:55,829
Mum, come back.

936
00:56:55,871 --> 00:56:57,497
(GROWLS)

937
00:57:01,835 --> 00:57:03,670
- Uh...
- (SNARLS)

938
00:57:03,754 --> 00:57:04,796
- Oh...
- (GROWLING)

939
00:57:08,759 --> 00:57:10,886
Mum, is that you?

940
00:57:11,970 --> 00:57:14,014
(ROARS)

941
00:57:14,056 --> 00:57:16,767
Uh... Mum?

942
00:57:18,477 --> 00:57:20,520
(WHINES)

943
00:57:23,523 --> 00:57:25,525
You changed.

944
00:57:25,609 --> 00:57:27,027
Like you were a...

945
00:57:27,945 --> 00:57:31,406
I mean, like you were a bear
on the inside.

946
00:57:31,865 --> 00:57:33,909
(WHINES AND SNORTS)

947
00:57:40,207 --> 00:57:41,208
(WISP CALLS)

948
00:57:41,291 --> 00:57:42,793
A wisp.

949
00:57:42,876 --> 00:57:45,545
- Mum!
- (WISP SQUEAKS)

950
00:57:45,587 --> 00:57:47,589
Stop it!

951
00:57:48,548 --> 00:57:50,217
Mum, no!

952
00:57:51,426 --> 00:57:52,469
(WISP CALLING)

953
00:57:52,552 --> 00:57:54,554
Mum...

954
00:57:55,847 --> 00:57:56,848
(GRUNTS)

955
00:57:59,393 --> 00:58:02,062
- (GROANS)
- Jings, crivens, help ma boab.

956
00:58:02,104 --> 00:58:04,606
Mum, I know you're scared,

957
00:58:04,690 --> 00:58:07,693
you're tired, you don't understand,

958
00:58:07,734 --> 00:58:10,988
but we've got to keep our heads.

959
00:58:11,071 --> 00:58:13,490
Just calm down.

960
00:58:13,991 --> 00:58:15,993
Listen.

961
00:58:19,705 --> 00:58:20,706
(FAINT WHISPERING)

962
00:58:25,043 --> 00:58:27,045
(FAINT WHISPERING CONTINUES)

963
00:58:35,721 --> 00:58:37,723
(WISP CALLS)

964
00:58:44,479 --> 00:58:45,939
They'll show us the way.

965
00:58:48,900 --> 00:58:50,902
(WISPS CALLING)

966
00:59:01,163 --> 00:59:03,790
(WISP CALLING)

967
00:59:14,217 --> 00:59:16,011
MERIDA: Mum, look.

968
00:59:22,851 --> 00:59:24,019
(WIND WHISTLES)

969
00:59:24,102 --> 00:59:25,979
(ELINOR BEAR GROANS)

970
00:59:26,063 --> 00:59:28,648
MERIDA: Why did the wisps
bring us here?

971
00:59:28,774 --> 00:59:30,275
(ELINOR BEAR MOANS)

972
00:59:35,447 --> 00:59:37,491
(ELINOR BEAR HUFFS AND SNORTS)

973
00:59:55,759 --> 00:59:58,178
Whoever they were,
they've been gone for a long, long time.

974
00:59:58,261 --> 01:00:00,764
(SCREAMS)

975
01:00:02,307 --> 01:00:03,850
(GROANS)

976
01:00:03,934 --> 01:00:06,686
- (WHINES)
- I'm fine, Mum.

977
01:00:06,770 --> 01:00:08,146
Just fine.

978
01:00:17,823 --> 01:00:19,825
It's, uh,

979
01:00:20,700 --> 01:00:21,785
a throne room.

980
01:00:23,578 --> 01:00:25,288
You suppose this could've
been the kingdom

981
01:00:25,372 --> 01:00:27,082
in that story you were telling me?

982
01:00:27,165 --> 01:00:30,001
- (MOANS)
- The one with the princes.

983
01:00:30,544 --> 01:00:31,878
(GROANS)

984
01:00:33,797 --> 01:00:35,382
One,

985
01:00:35,674 --> 01:00:36,758
two,

986
01:00:36,842 --> 01:00:38,343
three,

987
01:00:38,385 --> 01:00:40,220
four.

988
01:00:40,303 --> 01:00:42,180
The oldest.

989
01:00:42,472 --> 01:00:43,473
(GROANS)

990
01:00:45,142 --> 01:00:47,310
Split, like the tapestry.

991
01:00:48,895 --> 01:00:49,896
(GROWLING)

992
01:00:49,980 --> 01:00:51,356
(GASPS)

993
01:00:52,941 --> 01:00:56,278
The spell. It's happened before.

994
01:01:00,866 --> 01:01:03,368
"Strength of ten men."

995
01:01:04,703 --> 01:01:06,913
"Fate be changed."

996
01:01:09,082 --> 01:01:11,960
"Changed his fate."

997
01:01:13,044 --> 01:01:14,713
Oh, no.

998
01:01:14,754 --> 01:01:16,798
The prince became...

999
01:01:19,634 --> 01:01:21,094
(GROWLING)

1000
01:01:22,679 --> 01:01:24,681
- Mor'du.
- (ROARS)

1001
01:01:24,764 --> 01:01:26,099
(ROARING)

1002
01:01:28,310 --> 01:01:29,936
(SCREAMS)

1003
01:01:34,566 --> 01:01:36,109
(GROANING)

1004
01:01:36,193 --> 01:01:37,819
(ROARS)
(FABRIC TEARING)

1005
01:01:42,407 --> 01:01:44,201
(WHIMPERING)
(ROARS)

1006
01:01:52,334 --> 01:01:53,335
(SNARLS)

1007
01:01:59,424 --> 01:02:00,467
(MOANS)

1008
01:02:09,684 --> 01:02:10,936
(HUFFING AND PANTING)

1009
01:02:16,816 --> 01:02:18,777
(SCREAMS)

1010
01:02:20,278 --> 01:02:22,322
(CREAKING)

1011
01:02:25,909 --> 01:02:28,036
(MERIDA GROANS)

1012
01:02:30,121 --> 01:02:32,832
Mum, we need to get back to the castle.

1013
01:02:33,458 --> 01:02:36,795
If we don't hurry,
you'll become like Mor'du.

1014
01:02:36,836 --> 01:02:38,213
A bear!

1015
01:02:38,296 --> 01:02:40,465
A real bear. Forever!

1016
01:02:40,715 --> 01:02:44,302
- (WHINES)
- "Mend the bond torn by pride."

1017
01:02:45,095 --> 01:02:48,723
The witch gave us the answer.
The tapestry.

1018
01:02:57,482 --> 01:03:01,194
- (ELINOR GRUMBLES)
- Mum, do you have a better idea?

1019
01:03:02,487 --> 01:03:03,863
(GRUNTS)

1020
01:03:16,126 --> 01:03:17,419
(STRAINING)

1021
01:03:19,462 --> 01:03:20,839
That'll do.

1022
01:03:22,340 --> 01:03:24,342
(TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

1023
01:03:28,388 --> 01:03:30,307
(MEN SHOUTING)

1024
01:03:35,520 --> 01:03:38,231
No more talk. No more traditions.

1025
01:03:38,273 --> 01:03:39,691
We settle this now!

1026
01:03:39,733 --> 01:03:41,318
You're the King.

1027
01:03:41,401 --> 01:03:45,322
You decide which one of our sons
your daughter will marry.

1028
01:03:45,405 --> 01:03:48,491
None of your sons
are fit to marry my daughter.

1029
01:03:48,575 --> 01:03:51,578
Then our alliance is over!
This means war!

1030
01:03:52,746 --> 01:03:54,414
(SHOUTING)

1031
01:03:56,374 --> 01:03:58,084
They're gonna murder each other.

1032
01:03:58,126 --> 01:04:00,587
You've got to stop them
before it's too late.

1033
01:04:00,670 --> 01:04:02,297
(WHINES)

1034
01:04:02,380 --> 01:04:03,798
I know, I know!

1035
01:04:03,882 --> 01:04:06,593
But how do we get you through there
and up to the tapestry

1036
01:04:06,634 --> 01:04:08,678
with the lot of them
boiling over like that?

1037
01:04:09,429 --> 01:04:11,222
- (GRUNTS)
- Oh!

1038
01:04:15,143 --> 01:04:17,312
(SHOUTING)

1039
01:04:23,151 --> 01:04:24,611
(SHOUTING STOPS)

1040
01:04:27,781 --> 01:04:31,409
- What are you doing, lass?
- It's all right, Dad.

1041
01:04:31,451 --> 01:04:34,120
(CLEARS THROAT) I, um...

1042
01:04:34,871 --> 01:04:37,207
<i>I have...</i>

1043
01:04:37,832 --> 01:04:40,794
Well, you see, I...

1044
01:04:40,835 --> 01:04:43,463
I have been in conference
with the Queen.

1045
01:04:43,505 --> 01:04:46,424
- Is that so?
- Aye, it is.

1046
01:04:46,466 --> 01:04:48,718
- Well, where is she, then?
- She, uh...

1047
01:04:48,802 --> 01:04:50,929
How do we know that
this isn't some trick?

1048
01:04:50,970 --> 01:04:52,806
- I'd never...
- This is highly irregular.

1049
01:04:52,889 --> 01:04:54,808
- What are you playing at?
- Where is the Queen?

1050
01:04:54,849 --> 01:04:57,504
LORD MACINTOSH: We will not stand
for any more of this jiggery-pokery.

1051
01:04:57,519 --> 01:04:59,687
- That's right. Let's see her.
- Shut it!

1052
01:04:59,771 --> 01:05:00,772
(SILENCE)

1053
01:05:01,940 --> 01:05:03,066
(LAUGHS)

1054
01:05:03,358 --> 01:05:04,401
(CLEARS THROAT)

1055
01:05:04,484 --> 01:05:06,653
Well, I, uh...

1056
01:05:10,824 --> 01:05:11,825
Uh...

1057
01:05:16,287 --> 01:05:19,916
Once there was an ancient kingdom.

1058
01:05:20,166 --> 01:05:21,835
What is this?

1059
01:05:21,876 --> 01:05:25,422
That kingdom fell into war

1060
01:05:25,505 --> 01:05:27,590
and chaos and ruin...

1061
01:05:27,674 --> 01:05:30,760
Och, we've all heard that tale.
Lost kingdom.

1062
01:05:30,844 --> 01:05:32,429
Aye, but it's true.

1063
01:05:32,512 --> 01:05:36,182
I know now how one selfish act
can turn the fate of a kingdom.

1064
01:05:36,224 --> 01:05:37,669
LORD MACGUFFIN:
Bah, it's just a legend.

1065
01:05:37,684 --> 01:05:39,436
Legends are lessons.

1066
01:05:40,228 --> 01:05:42,313
They ring with truths.

1067
01:05:43,356 --> 01:05:44,941
Our kingdom is young.

1068
01:05:45,191 --> 01:05:47,318
Our stories are not yet legend.

1069
01:05:47,360 --> 01:05:50,530
But in them, our bond was struck.

1070
01:05:50,572 --> 01:05:52,699
Our clans were once enemies.

1071
01:05:52,782 --> 01:05:56,119
But when invaders threatened us
from the sea,

1072
01:05:56,202 --> 01:05:59,205
you joined together to defend our lands.

1073
01:05:59,747 --> 01:06:02,417
You fought for each other.

1074
01:06:02,500 --> 01:06:04,461
You risked everything for each other.

1075
01:06:05,378 --> 01:06:07,797
Lord MacGuffin, my dad saved your life,

1076
01:06:07,881 --> 01:06:10,425
stopping an arrow
as you ran to Dingwall's aid.

1077
01:06:10,508 --> 01:06:12,343
Aye, and I'll never forget it.

1078
01:06:12,385 --> 01:06:14,053
MERIDA: And, Lord Macintosh,

1079
01:06:14,137 --> 01:06:17,474
you saved my dad
when you charged in on heavy horse

1080
01:06:17,557 --> 01:06:19,267
and held off the advance.

1081
01:06:19,350 --> 01:06:23,396
And we all know how Lord Dingwall
broke the enemy line.

1082
01:06:23,480 --> 01:06:25,565
With a mighty throw of his spear!

1083
01:06:25,607 --> 01:06:27,525
I was aiming at you, you big tumshie.

1084
01:06:27,567 --> 01:06:28,985
(ALL LAUGH)

1085
01:06:29,360 --> 01:06:32,739
The story of this kingdom
is a powerful one.

1086
01:06:32,780 --> 01:06:35,366
My dad rallied your forces

1087
01:06:35,408 --> 01:06:37,785
and you made him your king.

1088
01:06:37,869 --> 01:06:41,956
It was an alliance forged in bravery
and friendship

1089
01:06:42,040 --> 01:06:43,791
and it lives to this day.

1090
01:06:43,875 --> 01:06:45,919
(ALL CHEERING)

1091
01:06:49,380 --> 01:06:51,841
But I've been selfish.

1092
01:06:51,925 --> 01:06:54,969
I tore a great rift in our kingdom.

1093
01:06:55,803 --> 01:06:57,889
There's no one to blame but me.

1094
01:06:58,723 --> 01:07:02,435
And I know now
that I need to amend my mistake

1095
01:07:03,603 --> 01:07:05,271
and mend our bond.

1096
01:07:06,814 --> 01:07:10,652
And so, there is the matter
of my betrothal.

1097
01:07:12,070 --> 01:07:15,406
I've decided to do what's right

1098
01:07:15,448 --> 01:07:16,616
and...

1099
01:07:17,450 --> 01:07:19,077
...and...

1100
01:07:19,786 --> 01:07:21,496
...and...

1101
01:07:22,497 --> 01:07:25,625
...break tradition.

1102
01:07:25,708 --> 01:07:27,168
(GASPING AND MUTTERING)

1103
01:07:32,006 --> 01:07:33,841
My mother...

1104
01:07:35,134 --> 01:07:37,804
...the Queen, feels...

1105
01:07:38,471 --> 01:07:41,641
...uh, in her heart

1106
01:07:41,724 --> 01:07:43,643
that I...

1107
01:07:45,353 --> 01:07:48,022
...that we be free to...

1108
01:07:49,399 --> 01:07:52,986
...write our own story...

1109
01:07:54,737 --> 01:07:58,992
...follow our hearts

1110
01:07:59,951 --> 01:08:03,580
and find love in our own time.

1111
01:08:07,333 --> 01:08:10,420
- That's (SNIFFS) beautiful.
- (ALL SNIFFLING)

1112
01:08:10,503 --> 01:08:13,881
The Queen and I put the decision
to you, my lords.

1113
01:08:14,757 --> 01:08:18,678
Might our young people decide
for themselves who they will love?

1114
01:08:18,720 --> 01:08:19,762
Huh?

1115
01:08:19,846 --> 01:08:23,016
Well, since you've obviously
made up your minds about this,

1116
01:08:23,057 --> 01:08:25,018
I have one thing to say.

1117
01:08:25,101 --> 01:08:27,645
- This is...
- A grand idea!

1118
01:08:27,687 --> 01:08:30,023
Give us our own say
in choosing our fate.

1119
01:08:30,064 --> 01:08:33,401
- What?
- Aye. Why shouldn't we choose?

1120
01:08:33,526 --> 01:08:35,570
But she's the princess.

1121
01:08:35,653 --> 01:08:38,656
I did not pick her out. It was your idea.

1122
01:08:38,698 --> 01:08:41,951
And you... You feel the same way?

1123
01:08:42,035 --> 01:08:47,040
(SPEAKS UNINTELLIGIBLY)

1124
01:08:47,081 --> 01:08:49,542
- Good?
- (GRUNTS)

1125
01:08:49,584 --> 01:08:50,877
(GIGGLES)

1126
01:08:52,170 --> 01:08:53,713
Well, that settles it.

1127
01:08:53,796 --> 01:08:58,551
Let these lads try and win her heart
before they win her hand.

1128
01:08:58,593 --> 01:08:59,927
If they can.

1129
01:09:00,011 --> 01:09:03,014
I say, the wee Dingwall
has a fighting chance.

1130
01:09:03,056 --> 01:09:05,516
Fine, then. Seems for once we agree.

1131
01:09:05,558 --> 01:09:08,603
- It was my idea in the first place.
- (ALL LAUGHING)

1132
01:09:08,686 --> 01:09:09,979
(SIGHS)

1133
01:09:13,858 --> 01:09:16,402
(ALL MUTTERING CONTENTEDLY)

1134
01:09:18,613 --> 01:09:20,531
Just like your mum.

1135
01:09:20,573 --> 01:09:21,866
You devil.

1136
01:09:24,911 --> 01:09:25,911
(GASPS)

1137
01:09:27,538 --> 01:09:30,583
Uh... Everyone to the cellar!

1138
01:09:30,667 --> 01:09:35,088
Let's crack open the King's
private reserve to celebrate!

1139
01:09:35,171 --> 01:09:36,839
(ALL CHEERING)

1140
01:09:36,923 --> 01:09:38,216
Oh.

1141
01:09:38,257 --> 01:09:40,635
(LAUGHS) Whoa, whoa, whoa.

1142
01:09:40,718 --> 01:09:42,929
Psst. Bring the tiny glasses.

1143
01:09:42,970 --> 01:09:44,972
(TALKING AND LAUGHING)

1144
01:09:48,768 --> 01:09:49,811
(SIGHS)

1145
01:09:49,894 --> 01:09:51,270
(MERIDA GIGGLES)

1146
01:09:51,562 --> 01:09:53,606
(SINGS HAPPILY)

1147
01:09:56,943 --> 01:09:58,277
Oh, the tapestry!

1148
01:10:01,072 --> 01:10:03,574
Mend the bond...

1149
01:10:04,784 --> 01:10:06,911
Mend the bond.

1150
01:10:06,953 --> 01:10:09,747
Stitch it up. This'll change you back.

1151
01:10:09,789 --> 01:10:12,125
We just need needle and thread.

1152
01:10:12,250 --> 01:10:13,292
(GRUNTS)

1153
01:10:17,463 --> 01:10:18,506
(GROWLS)

1154
01:10:18,589 --> 01:10:20,675
- Mum?
- (SNARLS)

1155
01:10:22,301 --> 01:10:24,178
Mum? Not now.

1156
01:10:24,262 --> 01:10:26,931
No. Please, not now.

1157
01:10:27,140 --> 01:10:28,141
(SNIFFING)

1158
01:10:28,224 --> 01:10:29,809
- Mum...
- (MEN LAUGHING)

1159
01:10:29,851 --> 01:10:31,102
- (GROWLS)
- Shh.

1160
01:10:32,937 --> 01:10:34,939
(SINGING JOVIALLY)

1161
01:10:38,317 --> 01:10:44,198
Elinor, dear, you'll never guess
who just solved our little suitor problem.

1162
01:10:44,282 --> 01:10:47,493
- (THUNDER RUMBLING)
- (FERGUS BREATHING HEAVILY)

1163
01:10:56,085 --> 01:10:57,420
Elinor!

1164
01:11:00,173 --> 01:11:04,010
It can't be true!
Elinor, answer me, lass!

1165
01:11:04,051 --> 01:11:06,179
Elinor!

1166
01:11:07,263 --> 01:11:09,599
- Merida.
- (SNARLING)

1167
01:11:09,682 --> 01:11:12,018
- What?
- Dad, no! It's not what you think.

1168
01:11:12,059 --> 01:11:14,145
- Merida, get back!
- No!

1169
01:11:14,187 --> 01:11:15,605
(GROWLING)

1170
01:11:16,522 --> 01:11:17,857
(YELLING)

1171
01:11:19,192 --> 01:11:21,277
No, Dad! Don't hurt her!

1172
01:11:22,195 --> 01:11:24,155
- Get out of here!
- (SCREAMS)

1173
01:11:24,197 --> 01:11:26,824
Merida! No!

1174
01:11:26,866 --> 01:11:27,867
(ROARS)

1175
01:11:28,034 --> 01:11:29,869
(YELLS)

1176
01:11:30,912 --> 01:11:33,289
- No!
- (ROARS)

1177
01:11:35,291 --> 01:11:36,584
(MOANS)

1178
01:11:39,462 --> 01:11:40,963
(GROANING)

1179
01:11:41,130 --> 01:11:43,716
- Mum.
- (WHINES)

1180
01:11:45,051 --> 01:11:46,594
(WHIMPERS)

1181
01:11:46,677 --> 01:11:51,557
It's all right. I'm all right. It's nothing.
It's just a little scratch. Mum!

1182
01:11:51,641 --> 01:11:53,601
- My liege!
- (ALL LAUGHING)

1183
01:11:53,684 --> 01:11:55,102
Fergus.

1184
01:11:56,312 --> 01:11:58,022
- Bear!
- (MOANING)

1185
01:11:58,064 --> 01:12:00,107
- (GROANS)
- Dad!

1186
01:12:00,191 --> 01:12:02,735
Count your stars, lass.
It almost had you. Are you hurt?

1187
01:12:02,819 --> 01:12:04,570
It's your wife, Elinor.

1188
01:12:04,612 --> 01:12:06,614
- (ELINOR WHINING)
- (MEN SHOUTING)

1189
01:12:08,407 --> 01:12:09,826
Close the gate!

1190
01:12:13,246 --> 01:12:15,373
- You're talking nonsense!
- It's the truth!

1191
01:12:15,414 --> 01:12:18,626
There was a witch and she
gave me a spell. It's not Mor'du.

1192
01:12:18,709 --> 01:12:21,128
Mor'du or not, I'll avenge your mother!

1193
01:12:21,212 --> 01:12:25,174
- I'll not risk losing you, too.
- MERIDA: No, Dad! Just listen to me.

1194
01:12:25,258 --> 01:12:27,927
Listen! You can't!

1195
01:12:27,969 --> 01:12:32,306
- It's your wife Elinor!
- Maudie, keep this and don't let her out.

1196
01:12:32,431 --> 01:12:34,851
- What about the bear?
- Just stay put.

1197
01:12:34,934 --> 01:12:36,269
(BARKING)

1198
01:12:37,645 --> 01:12:39,772
Oh...

1199
01:12:42,859 --> 01:12:44,527
(YELLING)

1200
01:12:51,325 --> 01:12:52,827
(GRUNTING)

1201
01:12:57,540 --> 01:12:58,541
(STRAINING)

1202
01:13:00,877 --> 01:13:01,878
(FRUSTRATED GRUNT)

1203
01:13:02,128 --> 01:13:04,797
Come on, you sorry bunch of galoots!
Yah!

1204
01:13:13,681 --> 01:13:15,057
Mum!

1205
01:13:15,141 --> 01:13:16,726
No.

1206
01:13:16,809 --> 01:13:18,352
No. Mum.

1207
01:13:21,355 --> 01:13:23,357
(WEEPING)

1208
01:13:36,370 --> 01:13:38,497
(GROANING)

1209
01:13:40,499 --> 01:13:41,918
Maudie. Maudie!

1210
01:13:42,001 --> 01:13:44,670
I need you!

1211
01:13:44,712 --> 01:13:46,172
Now!

1212
01:13:49,175 --> 01:13:51,802
(MERIDA GASPS) Oh, no.

1213
01:13:53,179 --> 01:13:55,097
Maudie.

1214
01:13:58,017 --> 01:13:59,268
(GASPS)

1215
01:14:00,811 --> 01:14:01,854
Get the key.

1216
01:14:09,195 --> 01:14:10,404
(GROWLING)

1217
01:14:10,488 --> 01:14:12,865
(SCREAMING)

1218
01:14:17,536 --> 01:14:18,579
<i>Yah!</i>

1219
01:14:18,871 --> 01:14:21,040
(SCREAMING)

1220
01:14:22,041 --> 01:14:23,417
Oh, Maudie!

1221
01:14:24,627 --> 01:14:25,628
(SCREAMING)

1222
01:14:28,214 --> 01:14:29,590
(BOTH SCREAMING)

1223
01:14:29,674 --> 01:14:32,218
Needle and thread. Needle and thread.
Needle and thread.

1224
01:14:36,889 --> 01:14:38,224
(BARKING)

1225
01:14:40,726 --> 01:14:41,978
(HUFFING AND GASPING)

1226
01:14:44,897 --> 01:14:46,899
(GRUNTS AND MOANS)

1227
01:14:50,444 --> 01:14:52,071
There he goes!

1228
01:14:52,154 --> 01:14:54,824
Needle and thread.
Needle and thread. Needle and thread.

1229
01:14:54,907 --> 01:14:56,158
Ah, you beauty!

1230
01:15:03,165 --> 01:15:05,126
(GASPS)

1231
01:15:05,209 --> 01:15:06,961
(STRAINING)

1232
01:15:12,425 --> 01:15:14,010
(SHRIEKS)

1233
01:15:16,846 --> 01:15:18,764
(GASPS)

1234
01:15:19,098 --> 01:15:20,474
(WHIMPERING)

1235
01:15:22,977 --> 01:15:26,188
One, two... Huh?

1236
01:15:27,106 --> 01:15:28,149
(GASPS)

1237
01:15:30,109 --> 01:15:31,944
- (THUD)
- MAUDIE: Oh!

1238
01:15:31,986 --> 01:15:33,195
(CUB GROWLING)

1239
01:15:33,529 --> 01:15:34,530
(GASPS)

1240
01:15:34,947 --> 01:15:35,948
(WHINING)

1241
01:15:52,298 --> 01:15:54,300
(CRIES OUT)

1242
01:15:55,509 --> 01:15:57,595
Steady, Hamish.

1243
01:15:57,636 --> 01:15:59,638
FERGUS: There he goes.

1244
01:16:01,057 --> 01:16:03,726
- (GRUNTS)
- (DOGS BARKING)

1245
01:16:05,519 --> 01:16:06,562
(GROANS)

1246
01:16:06,645 --> 01:16:08,355
(MEN SHOUTING IN DISTANCE)

1247
01:16:09,774 --> 01:16:11,776
FERGUS: We've got his track!

1248
01:16:12,401 --> 01:16:13,944
- (BARKING)
- (MOANS)

1249
01:16:16,530 --> 01:16:18,699
- Back, back, back!
- Get him!

1250
01:16:19,325 --> 01:16:20,325
(GROANS)

1251
01:16:22,620 --> 01:16:24,622
Angus! Easy, laddie.

1252
01:16:26,040 --> 01:16:27,750
(CRIES OUT)

